( afp , washington , 2 ) usa today reported that pyongyang authorities authorized a us delegation , including top nuclear scientists , to visit north korea 's yongbyon nuclear facilities next week .
the bush administration has approved a us delegation 's scheduled visit to north korea from january 6 to 10 , members of the delegation told the us press today .
this will be the first foreign delegation to visit a disputed nuclear facility in north korea since un inspectors were deported from north korea a year ago .
the us delegation includes a chinese expert from stanford university , two senate foreign policy assistants , and a former state department official in charge of dealings with pyongyang .
nuclear experts mohkel and hekel of the delegation led the us national laboratory in the 1985 - 1997 period in which they were the first to develop atomic bombs .
earlier , north korea informed the us embassy in beijing that pyongyang was preparing to attend the stalled second round of six - party talks on the nuclear crisis on the korean peninsula .
us officials pointed out early this week that pyongyang had indicated that it was ready to participate in the six - party talks to be held at the beginning of the year .
no conclusion was reached at the conclusion of the first round of six - party talks in beijing in august last year . north korea subsequently criticized the negotiations as " useless . "
the second round of six - party talks was originally scheduled for last december , but the talks were forced to be postponed to early this year because of differences in positions on the issue .
washington wants north korea to abandon its nuclear program unilaterally , while pyongyang insists on providing the united states with a legally binding security guarantee as a condition for it to give up its nuclear weapons development program .
