( agence france - presse , tokyo , 5th ) - japanese prime minister junichiro koizumi vowed at a press conference on the first working day after the new year holiday that he would continue to promote economic reforms this year . he said : " although the economic situation is still difficult , we can finally see signs of recovery . "
koizumi stressed : " i will stand fast to my reform policy and continue to promote reform .
continued reform efforts will promote economic recovery . "
koizumi said he would particularly focus on congress ' deliberations on privatization of postal services this year .
he said , " we will eventually take action on privatization of postal services . this is the main axis of economic reform . "
koizumi added that he hoped to submit the bill to congress early next year .
koizumi has promised to privatize the postal service with 280,000 employees by 2007 .
japan 's postal service sector is regarded as the world 's largest bank by japan 's 355 - trillion yen ( 3.3 - trillion dollars ) savings and insurance fund .
however , this large - scale plan still faces strong opposition from conservative congressmen .
the plan began when koizumi served as the post minister in 1993 .
analysts said the japanese economy is expected to maintain a steady growth of about two percent this year , but the japanese public may still be worried about further pay cuts and lay - offs .
while many companies are continuing to rectify to ensure their profits , the unemployment rate in japan is still higher than five percent .
us begins taking photos of foreign visitors
( agence france - presse , washington , 5th ) - singapore , the largest airport in asia , supports new measures taken by u . s . today to take photographs and keep fingerprints of foreign visitors while additional air policemen are deployed to deal with terrorist threats .
washington has been forced to cancel flights to and from the united states in the past week amid heightened flight safety concerns around the world .
the new measure applies only to foreign visitors requiring visas to enter the united states , and it is generally expected that the number of such visitors will reach 23 million this year .
the homeland security department , which is responsible for implementing the " us visitors and migrants show technology " project , pointed out that citizens of most 28 countries in europe may exempt from the above procedures .
immigration groups accused the plan of violating civil rights and a step toward building a monitoring society . homeland security secretary ridge vigorously defended the plan .
ridge said in an interview with the nbc , " one of the primary responsibilities of any government is to ensure border security . we are carrying out this program well . i think it will not go wrong at all . in fact , no one will care about it in only about 15 seconds . "
by 2005 , all entry points of the land , sea , and air will be equipped with fingerprint techniques .
all us visas and passports will be included in the " bioidentification signs " including photos and fingerprints .
prior to the implementation of the plan , the united states raised the level of alert against terrorist threat throughout the united states last december .
