yin yongkuan made the remarks after washington rejected pyongyang 's latest offer of major concessions in exchange for a freeze on nuclear weapons , saying the two sides still had to resolve their serious differences before the nuclear talks .
yin yongkuan said : the issue of the timetable for the six participating countries has actually ruled out the possibility of resuming the six - nation talks in january .
however , he did not provide any clues as to why the new round of talks could be delayed until june .
russian deputy foreign minister roosevelt attributed this to the hard - line attitudes of the united states and north korea .
he participated in the first round of six - nation talks in beijing in august last year .
after meeting with senior chinese officials yesterday , roosevelt said to the interfax news agency : " the reason is still a sample of the past - - mutual distrust and the demands made by both sides are too heavy . "
after north korea once again asked the united states to make a concession before the new round of six - nation talks , yin yongkuan proposed the possibility that the talks would be postponed for a long time .
