indian prime minister vajpayee and pakistani president musharraf held their first talks on the possibility of a nuclear war between the two countries in 2002 at the edge of the summit yesterday .
the hostility between the two big powers of the south asian association for regional cooperation has obstructed regional development and the leaders of all participating countries were encouraged by the driving force for peace clearly promoted by the historic meeting between india and pakistan .
" i think the positions of both india and pakistan have changed in a clear - cut manner and the two countries are moving toward peace , " military analyst mashad told afp .
pakistani prime minister jamali officially announced the conclusion of the summit and praised the important agreements on counter - terrorism , alleviating poverty and establishing a regional free trade zone in 2006 .
he also praised the summit as " injecting new vitality into regional cooperation " .
heads of state and foreign ministers of bangladesh , bhutan , india , malta , nepal , pakistan and sri lanka signed at the summit the south asian free trade zone agreement , the social charter , the anti-poverty program , the anti-terrorism agreement , and the islamabad declaration .
