" if the government fails to fulfill its duties to protect the rights of citizens and to hold free elections , continuing to govern will not become a choice , " he said .
iranian governors from 27 provinces have also spread the message that they will resign collectively . sources close to president khatami disclosed that at least 10 ministers have been ready to resign .
however , the media denied reports that the moderate president khatami was preparing to resign .
angry reformists continue to stage a sit - in demonstration on the third day of the parliament building , and said that they would not hesitate to sit down in the next few weeks .
83 reformists were deprived of their qualifications and could not run for reelection .
iranian parliamentarians have challenged the constitutional guardianship board and asked it to take back the ruling that they have lost their election qualifications , the iranian news agency said .
the board of custody of the constitution consists of 12 people , is a non - elected political supervision organ , and is also the fortress of anti - religious right - wing forces .
