nt dollar 's appreciation will not affect business confidence in new zealand
( agence france - presse , wellington , the 15th ) - according to the latest survey report released by the new zealand economic research center , business circles are still very confident about new zealand despite the negative impact of the new zealand currency 's ups and downs .
the report pointed out that enterprises that were pessimistic about the business environment for the next six months accounted for only 2% , in contrast , and the figures for the first two quarters were 3% and 20% respectively .
the research center pointed out that according to various indicators of the survey report , the economy grew steadily in the fourth quarter of last year , and business activities themselves increased by 31% .
however , according to the forward - looking indicators , new zealand 's economic growth is expected to " continue to decline moderately in the next few quarters . "
the rapid appreciation of the new zealand dollar in the past three months has widened the confidence gap between exporters and non - exporters , said new zealand 's economic research center economist jadona .
about 11 per cent of manufacturers and construction exporters expect a recession in the next six months and 14 per cent of non - exporters are optimistic about their business outlook for the next six months .
the new currency has appreciated by 30% in the past two years .
