japan sets 10 - year budget target
( agence france - presse , tokyo , 16th ) - japanese finance minister sadakazu tanigaki said today that he believed the world 's second largest economy would be able to shake off a " financial crisis " and rectify finances within 10 years .
sadakazu tanigaki said the central and local governments ' combined deficits would total 5 percent of japan 's gross domestic product , which could be removed within 10 years if the average annual decrease was 0.5 percent .
he told a group of reporters : " japan 's financial situation is still in a crisis .
in terms of ( fiscal ) mobility and reserves , our situation is the worst among major industrial countries . "
by march 2014 , japan set a target of turning its " primitive deficits " into " primitive surpluses " - - to achieve a balance of finance at various levels for the first time in more than 20 years .
this is the first time that the japanese government led by prime minister junichiro koizumi has given japan a " primitive surplus " . under such circumstances , tax revenue exceeds non - payment expenses .
the previous surplus in japan ended its six - year surplus in the year before the end of march 1992 .
tokyo stock exchange approves newborns application for listing
( afp , tokyo , 16 february ) the tokyo stock exchange said today that it has approved newborns to apply for listing on the tokyo stock exchange . the new bank 's stocks will begin trading on 19 february .
the newly reissued bank , which was taken over by the us investment fund , will be publicly issued for the first time . it will provide 242 - million shares for domestic investors in japan , as well as 195 - million shares for overseas investors .
the initial public offering price will be determined on february 9 .
the newco has also prepared a possible surplus of 36.3 million shares to cater for the possibility that some subscription can not be completed .
the predecessor of newco is the long - term credit bank of japan . after the bankruptcy of the long - term credit bank of japan in 1998 , it was turned over to the state - owned sector . the newly renovated bank has already provided retail financial services .
newborns estimated that for the year ending march 2004 , group profit could reach 65 billion yen ( 613 million dollars ) , 22.6% up from the previous year , with a 76.5 billion yen growth , with total revenues down 13% to 175 billion yen .
the newborns also said that the total amount of bad creditor 's rights as at the end of last month was 132.3 billion yen , down from 154.2 billion yen three months ago .
