iraqi guerrillas fight us helicopters with high - tech weapons
( agence france - presse , washington , 18th ) - senior u . s . military figures said that iraqi resistance forces attacked u . s . helicopters with more and more sophisticated weapons .
a group of senior military officials familiar with a classified military report told the new york times today that a confidential military research report found iraqi guerrillas attacked american helicopters by using rocket - propelled grenades and more advanced thermal tracking and surface - to - air missiles .
they said that this was a study conducted by iraq this month before its three attacks on us military helicopters , but the latest three attacks would only serve to confirm the conclusions of the research report .
the main purpose of this military research report is to provide a method for us pilots to avoid attacks by iraqi guerrillas , and officials concerned are unwilling to discuss new findings .
however , looking at the method of a new wave of attacks in iraq , we cannot help worrying that iraqi guerrillas have carefully studied the combat pattern of us planes .
researchers found that iraqi guerrillas used salem - 16 shoulder - to - shoulder missiles more than once , and this is particularly worrisome .
this kind of missile with sophisticated navigation systems makes it very difficult for pilots to avoid .
" every time our aircraft was shot down , it was a great victory in the strategy of the enemy , " a senior us air officer in the persian gulf region said .
not only did the news reports wantonly spread , but the enemy also made a verdict of defeat . therefore , the enemy considers this a very useful trick . "
since 25 october last year , nine us military helicopters have been shot down or crashed , killing at least 49 us soldiers .
