vietnam 's health officials announced earlier that the sixth case of bird flu had died , bringing the death toll of bird flu to at least six and raising concerns over the spread of the virus and the human problem .
prior to this boy , bird flu hatch 571 was tested positive and confirmed to be infected .
ho chi minh city , jan 22 , 2007 ( afp ) the boy died of illness in the second children 's hospital in ho chi minh city on january 22 , health minister nguyen dy nien told afp today .
he was sent to hospital on the 19 th for respiratory symptoms .
the who also said that at present , it is following closely with vietnamese authorities the development of the epidemic .
another vietnamese health official pointed out that a pair of sisters in a hospital in hanoi also died of serious respiratory illness on the 22 nd . the health authorities suspected that the two were also victims of bird flu .
millions of poultry hit by bird flu in indonesia
( agence france - presse , jakarta , 25th ) - indonesia 's ministry of agriculture announced today that bird flu has caused the death of several million chickens . however , no human infection has been reported so far .
the head of the department of animal affairs of the agriculture ministry , sudato sodato , told the public that no one in indonesia is infected with the deadly disease so far .
seven countries in asia have reported bird flu outbreaks , and six people in vietnam have died of the disease .
indonesian officials said earlier that bird flu generally infected poultry in java and gaza last november was a new city disease .
this morning , spokesman for the ministry of agriculture joseph prueher said that there is no indication so far of a bird flu outbreak in indonesia .
he told afp in the evening that it was still unclear whether this wave of epidemic caused the 571 virus .
most of vietnam 's bird flu deaths were caused by the hatching 571 virus .
the spokesman said that with influenza a in the new town , 4.7 million poultry had died since november last year .
about 60 percent of them died of illness in the city .
he said he had not ordered an immediate culling operation .
the indonesian state news agency quoted sudato as saying that authorities had used british and australian blood to test the strain but the test results could not be released until wednesday or wednesday , and that the government would submit a report to relevant international organizations .
snow covers northern europe , causes traffic and transport chaos
( agence france - presse , paris , 29 th ) heavy snowstorms cover half of western europe and northern europe , causing great traffic and railway confusion and forcing hundreds of flights between britain , germany and denmark to be cancelled .
in london , a spokesman for the haas airport said more than 200 flights were cancelled last night due to accumulated snow , and 80 flights were suspended early this morning .
snow has also affected the other two airports near london , with 18 flights cancelled due to weather conditions .
in germany , the winter weather has led to the cancellation of at least 60 flights to frankfurt international airport , and frankfurt airport is germany 's largest airport .
air traffic may be affected by weather conditions throughout the day , while the rest of the flights will fly to frankfurt , transport authorities said .
paris , march 6 , 2007 ( afp ) road traffic restrictions have been lifted in france following a snowstorm last night , but similar measures have been lifted in other parts of france this morning .
all services at the main paris airport were reported to be in normal condition and flights were delayed at the charles de gaulle airport yesterday due to accumulated snow and fog .
however , the paris airport authority suggests that passengers on board the air must first find out whether their flights take off and land on schedule before leaving home .
most parts of france are covered by white snow , apart from the central coast of the country .
both taiwan and japan are democratic countries and have the obligation and responsibility to make joint efforts to consolidate democracy in asia .
in order to publicize the value of democracy , the chinese government will establish the " taiwan democratic foundation " in the near future . international political party cooperation is one of the priorities of its work .
the dpp hopes to share its experience in democratic development with other democratic parties in order to contribute to peace , stability and prosperity in asia and realize the ideal of a " democratic union in asia " at an early date .
today , when the international situation changes with each passing day , the regional forces will change a slight move in one part of the situation as a whole , and every country 's security is tested .
as far as the asia - pacific region is concerned , since the united states launched a war against iraq last month , north korea , which regards itself as an independent nuclear power , has test - fired missiles several times , flying over japan 's territorial air space , and china has long actively expanded its armaments and deployed ballistic missiles aimed at taiwan .
all this has already posed a serious threat to the security of taiwan , japan , and the asia - pacific region .
only formal security mechanisms will be needed to discuss and resolve these issues related to the consolidation of democracy and security .
it goes without saying that today 's meeting is the first official dialogue on security issues between the dpp and other diet members of japan 's ruling party .
i also hope that in addition to the bilateral dialogues between taiwan and japan , the united states , japan , the rok , and other neighboring countries in the asia - pacific region will be able to cooperate in promoting the establishment of a " security dialogue mechanism " and support taiwan 's participation in regional multilateral dialogues in order to implement the spirit of " cooperative security " .
today is an important moment encouraging us to continue to advance on the road of reform , and we would like to give our greatest affirmation to all comrades in the party who can embody the will of our party and make concerted efforts to achieve the reform objective .
" the withdrawal of a political party from the radio , film and television media " is the most basic requirement for implementing the media reform . it is also the consistent ideal of the dpp . the ruling party can only speed up the pace of reform , not obstruct or burden .
we also know that to promote this goal , the party 's public affairs comrades should take the lead in withdrawing from the media operation . this is a small step in the media reform , but it is also a key step .
in the period of enforcing martial law in the past , many comrades within the party , in order to strive for the space of opening up to the outside world , have thrown themselves into such arduous tasks as setting up the fourth station and local radio station in the hope of breaking through the existing limitations and increasing the capacity to promote the transformation of the media 's environment .
for example , comrade cai tongrong did a lot of painstaking work in those years in order to give birth to the fourth wireless tv station , and finally he had the birth of " popular support . "
this move has a considerable impact on the media as a whole . in particular , it has broken down the long - standing monopoly of the three television stations and created more space for cable tv stations to promote their development .
however , we must understand that because of the limitations of the historical environment and because there are many extraordinary things in the process of promoting reform , the space of media space has become completely open and free today , representing that the tasks for the current stage have been accomplished and that there are bound to be some sacrifices in order to continue the process of reform .
the standing committee announced that all the party and government comrades would withdraw from the radio , film , and television media operation before 5 september to take the lead in fulfilling their commitments to the people .
we are very pleased to see that the party 's ideals and objectives are taken into account , including cai tongrong , chang chun - hung , zhou qingyu , hou shuisheng , gao mengding , huang naima , and shen gongming , who have made a lot of contributions to the democratic movement .
ruling the country is not enjoying the power , but increasing the sense of responsibility .
in the process of the dpp 's administration , there are bound to be setbacks and ups and downs . we will always be able to challenge the power to advance and lead taiwan in building projects to deepen democracy . at the same time , we will merge with the universal values of global democracy , peace , and prosperity .
this is because we always believe that the people are the masters of this country . the responsibility of the democratic progressive party is to upgrade the pioneering spirit of " honesty , diligence , and loving the native land " to the bright prospect of " reform , progress , and good life " and lay a foundation for lasting peace and stability for the 23 million taiwan people .
for a long time , the dpp has played the role of " separation of the government " in the efforts to develop taiwan 's diplomacy and has achieved brilliant results .
despite the continuous suppression of the chinese communists , we have never retired because our destiny is in our own hands , and even without rich resources , the dpp is still advancing step by step , thus expanding taiwan 's international participation space .
" diversified diplomacy " is the principal axis of the dpp 's overall foreign policy . in the past year , we have successfully exchanged experiences and exchanged experiences with countries in the region , with the " asian free and democratic union " as our platform , targeting the economic challenges of the east asian region , democratic reform of political parties , removing money rights politics , resolving globalization and poverty , promoting political propaganda and communication , and youth 's participation in political affairs .
in march next year , i will also officially take over the presidency of the " asian freedom and democracy union . " i hope to create more opportunities for taiwan to contribute to the international community in its capacity as the leader of an international organization .
in addition , the dpp has also actively participated in relevant affairs since it became an official member of the " international freedom union " last year .
in addition to sending officials to serve as human rights commissioner at the secretariat of the london headquarters , they will also cooperate with other member parties and hold political reform seminars in central and south america and europe .
on 28 september , our party celebrated its 17 th birthday .
the 17 - year - old democratic progressive party has always adhered to the ideal of democracy and is full of strength for reform and progress .
it is precisely because we have all along stood on the side of democratic reform that we can gain the trust of the people of taiwan , and the responsibility and mission we will shoulder in the future will be even more serious and heavy .
when we took over the burden of being the ruling party three years ago , the ruling party of the past tried to make a roundabout trip six times to revise the constitution .
from the 1991 handling of a full - scale election of the national assembly , handling of direct presidential elections in 1994 , freezing the provincial government 's organization in 1997 , and putting the national people 's congress in a very serious position by 2000 , these tortuous course of constitutional revision is actually the track of strengthening the legitimacy of sovereignty and democracy of the people of taiwan .
if we regard being directly elected by the president in 1996 as the most important symbol of taiwan becoming a sovereign and independent democratic country , then by 2006 this " complete " country is already 10 years old .
after 10 years of practice , we must think about what we will pursue as a democratic country with independent sovereignty .
i must say that in the next stage , we should further pursue the deepening of democracy and a more efficient constitutional system in order to lead the taiwan people in accepting the grim challenge of the new century .
asia is the largest continent in the world , with an area accounting for nearly 30 percent of the world 's total land area . at present , its population accounts for about 60 percent of the world 's total , and its total economic volume accounts for one fourth of the world 's total . it should and can make outstanding contributions to world peace and development .
asia has a long and splendid culture . the huang he and the yangtze river valley , the indian river and the henghe river valley , the youngest river , and the chryvas valley are famous places of human civilization .
over a long historical process , the people of asia have written a brilliant chapter for the development of human civilization .
in modern times , asia has gone through many vicissitudes of life and suffered repeated hardships . the people of all countries have made unremitting efforts to liberate and develop asia and scored tremendous achievements .
however , there is still a long way to go in order to bring about a new rise and rejuvenation in asia .
to strengthen cooperation , promote development , and bring about a pent - up is the inevitable course for the rise and rejuvenation of asia , and is also where the fundamental interests of the people of asia lie .
under the new situation in the new century , the development of asia is facing new opportunities .
peace and development are still the main themes of the present age , and the overall peaceful international environment has provided favorable external conditions for the development of asia .
economic globalization is developing in depth , the scientific and technological revolution in the world is advancing by leaps and bounds , and the optimization , reorganization , and industrial transfer of international production factors are being accelerated . this is beneficial for asian countries to utilize international capital , introduce advanced technology , open up international markets , and promote their own economic development .
asia is rich in resources and has a vast market . it is a region with the greatest economic vitality in the world today , and its development potential is enormous .
there are many people and not well - developed people . these are the two major national conditions of china .
china has 1.3 - billion people . no matter how small the issue is , taking 1.3 - billion people as a gift will become a very big problem . no matter how much financial and material resources it is , it will become very low per capita .
this is something that the chinese leaders must firmly remember at any time .
to solve the problem of 1.3 billion people , we cannot rely on others but on ourselves .
since the founding of the people 's republic of china , we have made great achievements in construction . meanwhile , we have also made detours and missed some opportunities .
since the beginning of reform and opening up in 1978 , we have finally found a correct road of development .
this is : the chinese people independently build socialism with chinese characteristics .
the essence of this road is to mobilize all positive factors , liberate and develop the productive forces , and respect and protect the freedom of the chinese people in pursuing happiness .
china 's reform and opening up , from the rural areas to cities , and from the economic field to the political , cultural , and social fields .
in the final analysis , every step of its deepening is aimed at giving free rein to the vitality of all labor , knowledge , technology , management , and capital and vying with one another to break out , so that all sources of creating social wealth will flow in full .
in recent years , profound changes are taking place in the world , science and technology are changing with each passing day , the level of the world 's productive forces is constantly improving , and the world market is forging closer ties , thus creating historical opportunities for the development of all countries .
however , it is noteworthy that power politics , regional conflicts , terrorism , infectious diseases , and environmental deterioration are still threatening world stability and development .
the negative impact of economic globalization has increased the risk and price of developing countries ' economic and social development , and some developing countries are even facing the danger of being marginalized .
at present , although the world economy is gradually recovering , it still faces many uncertain factors .
the doha round of multilateral trade talks has suffered setbacks , and trade protectionism and other complicated factors have added to the difficulties of developing countries .
what is gratifying is that the vast numbers of developing countries are forging ahead in an active manner , are determined to carry out reform with keen determination , and are making great efforts to make the country prosperous .
on the international stage , relying on the non-aligned movement and the group of 77 , the developing countries have strengthened unity and cooperation , made important contributions to safeguarding their own legitimate rights and interests and changing their irrational international political and economic order , and become an important force in promoting democratization of international relations .
at the same time , the exchange and cooperation between the developing countries has also yielded rich results and economic exchanges between them have become even more frequent .
south - south cooperation has been constantly enriched , perfected , and updated from the antara mountain range to the mekong river , from the amur union to the establishment of the african union , and from the form and mechanism to the means .
the past year was also a year in which the friendly and cooperative relations between china and canada continued to develop in an all - round way .
the trade volume between the two countries has maintained a momentum of growth , and the total volume of trade is close to $ 10 billion .
high - level exchanges have been frequent ; a number of important political figures , such as the canadian foreign minister , the minister of defense , the minister of the environment , and the minister of international cooperation , have visited china one after another ; and china 's supreme court president , commerce minister , and other senior officials have also paid visits to canada . more importantly , the two premiers have successfully exchanged visits with each other .
premier wen jiabao 's recent visit to canada has the significance of carrying forward the cause pioneered by our predecessors and forging ahead into the future , and has injected new vitality into the further development of sino - canadian relations , thus laying a solid foundation for the continuous development of friendly cooperation in all fields between the two countries in depth and in breadth .
china and canada will continue to strengthen cooperation in the political , economic , cultural , educational , scientific , and technological fields , and strive to achieve the goal of doubling the total volume of bilateral trade in 2010 .
all overseas chinese compatriots and friends ,
although you live abroad , you always have your heart in your hometown , are concerned about the construction and development of the motherland , and at every crucial moment you always worry about the worries of the people of the motherland , enjoy the happiness of the people of the motherland , and swing with the pulse of the motherland .
last year , after sars and floods occurred in some areas of china , you expressed your deep concern and best wishes to the people of the motherland through the internet , letters , telephone calls , and donations . chinese from all walks of life have held many large donations and charity performances . after the successful launch of the " shenzhou v " manned space flight , you have sent congratulatory messages , letters , and greeting cards one after another . everyone feels proud of china 's achievements in aerospace science and technology .
