first , political mutual trust should be strengthened and strategic cooperation deepened .
china and france , as permanent members of the un security council , are both countries with important influence on international affairs .
our two countries agree to promote multi - polarization of the world , advocate safeguarding the authority of the united nations , and are willing to promote the establishment of a new international political and economic order that conforms with the will of the peoples of all countries .
the two countries share a broad consensus and common interests in dealing with various challenges facing mankind and in properly handling major international affairs .
we are willing to strengthen dialogue and consultation with france on major issues such as fighting terrorism , preventing proliferation , cracking down on transnational crime , promoting common development , and strengthening the role of the united nations , and carry out close cooperation with france in safeguarding world peace and promoting common development .
second , it is necessary to strengthen economic and trade cooperation and achieve mutually beneficial and mutually complementary results .
china is the largest developing country in the world , and is making all - out efforts to carry out modernization and has a vast market .
france is a developed country with a leading edge in economic and scientific and technological fields .
the economies of our two countries are strongly complementary , and there is great potential for economic and trade cooperation .
since the founding of new china , the chinese government has always attached great importance to developing relations with africa and formulated a series of principles and policies .
we have always upheld the five principles of peaceful coexistence , respected the african countries for independently choosing their own political systems and paths of development , provided as much assistance as possible to african countries , carried out economic and technological cooperation , supported the unity and cooperation among african countries , supported the international community in attaching importance to peace and development in africa , supported african countries in taking part in international affairs on an equal footing , strengthened consultation and cooperation between china and african countries , and jointly safeguarded the rights and interests of developing countries .
sino - african friendship goes back to ancient times and enjoys popular support .
since the founding of new china , we have always firmly supported the cause of national liberation in africa and sincerely assisted african countries in developing their national economies .
chinese experts , doctors , teachers , and workers sent to africa work side by side with the local people , live together in friendship and love .
in international affairs , china and the african countries understand and support each other and have become mutually trusted partners .
the chinese people will never forget that china smoothly regained its legitimate seat in the united nations at the 26th un general assembly in 1971 precisely with the energetic support of the vast numbers of developing countries , including african countries .
in recent years , mutual political trust between china and africa at various levels and between personnel of various circles has been deepened . economic and trade cooperation has been fruitful . friendly exchanges in the cultural , educational , public health , scientific , technological , and sports fields have developed vigorously . the china - africa cooperation forum , which was founded at the beginning of the century , has set up a new platform for the development of sino - african relations and for deepening cooperation .
china and africa have decided to establish a new long - term , stable , equal , and mutually beneficial partnership , and sino - african friendly cooperation has entered a new stage of comprehensive development .
seven years after nixon 's visit to china and the publication of the shanghai communique , the carter administration accepted the chinese stand on the taiwan issue and established sino - us diplomatic relations .
this incident and deng xiaoping 's successful visit to the united states have opened a new chapter in sino - us relations .
in the early days of reagan 's administration , there were fierce confrontations between china and the united states on the taiwan issue .
through arduous negotiations , the two governments issued the famous " 17 august " communique in 1982 , and reached an agreement on the gradual resolution of the issue of arms sales to taiwan .
the shanghai communique , the sino - us communique on the establishment of diplomatic relations , and the " 17 august " communique jointly constitute the political cornerstone of sino - us relations .
in the 10 years since the establishment of diplomatic relations , sino - us relations have , on the whole , been stable , and exchanges and cooperation in various fields have increased , despite the struggle between the two countries on the taiwan issue .
in the 1980s and early 1990s , drastic changes took place in eastern europe , the soviet union disintegrated , and the cold war ended . the most profound changes have taken place in the international situation since world war ii .
the united states took the lead in imposing sanctions on china , announcing the sale of 150 - 16 fighter planes , linking the human rights issue with most favored nation treatment , and allowing lee teng - hui to visit the united states , with the result that sino - us relations fell to a low ebb .
with the rapid development of china 's economy , china 's international status has been raised continuously .
more and more people in the united states have come to realize that the improvement and development of sino - us relations are in the interests of both the united states and china .
half a year ago , in this hall , we successfully activated the process of the six - party talks and set the direction for a peaceful resolution of the nuclear issue .
over the past six months , the various parties have carried out incessant dialogue and consultations , made a great deal of in - depth preparations for a new round of talks , and through this process , enhanced understanding of each other 's stances .
at present , all the parties are looking forward to discussing substantive issues in the second round of talks and to achieving concrete results , they agree to resolve mutual concerns through concerted and consistent steps , and they hope to maintain the peace process opened up by the six - party talks .
all these constitute an important foundation for our talks today .
the significance of the second round of talks lies in starting discussions on substantive issues , which marks a new step forward in the peace talks process .
the current round of talks will involve the establishment of a specific objective for resolving the nuclear issue , the exploration of first - stage measures for resolving the nuclear issue , and the study of ways for the progress of the sustained talks .
as the talks are going deeper , we will still deal with more difficulties and meet more challenges , but this is precisely the responsibility bestowed on us by history as well as the hope placed on us by the international community .
our six - party meeting here represents the strong political aspiration of the governments and peoples of the six countries to seek peace .
the purpose of our talks was to expand consensus , not highlight differences , and to resolve problems rather than intensify contradictions .
the chinese side believes that all sides are aware of the peace mission on their shoulders and , with a constructive attitude , the spirit of cooperation and understanding , respect each other , display flexibility , and narrow the gap .
after more than three days of consultations , the agenda for the second round of six - party talks in beijing completed .
i would like to express my gratitude to the governments , leaders , representatives , and working personnel of various countries for their contributions to this cause .
if the first round of talks decided on the goal of denuclearization of the peninsula , then the significance of this round of talks was to hold substantial dialogues and to make a new step toward realizing the general goal of denuclearization .
during the talks , all the parties conducted in - depth and constructive discussions , explored methods and steps for resolving problems with wisdom and rationality , put forward valuable ideas , and made positive policy statements .
the talks achieved a series of useful results , and in particular reached consensus on the formation of a working group for the next round of talks , which is of great significance to promoting the process of peace talks .
dear colleagues , peace and development are the themes of our great era .
the people of the six countries you represent need peace , desire peace and love peace , and the people of all countries in the world want peace , love peace and love peace .
over the past three days , the international community has paid close attention to beijing and the diaoyutai , hoping for the talks .
some people may believe that the results of the talks are not great enough and that the process is not fast enough .
my view is that this round of talks started when the parties concerned lacked mutual trust and there was an increase in the gap between them in their positions .
the chinese government 's stand on the taiwan issue is consistent , that is , it adheres to the basic principle of " peaceful reunification , and one country , two systems . "
to this end , we have exerted every effort , displayed the greatest sincerity , and done a lot of work .
however , our efforts have met with provocation from the taiwan authorities and the " taiwan independence " forces .
we respect the democratic demands of the taiwan people , but we oppose the taiwan authorities and the " taiwan independence " forces engaging in " taiwan independence " activities in the name of democracy and separating taiwan from the motherland .
the reason why we have clearly demonstrated our determination and will to safeguard the reunification of the motherland is to maintain peace and stability in the taiwan strait region .
we have said that as long as there is hope on the front line , we will do our utmost to realize the reunification of the motherland by peaceful means .
we appreciate president bush 's reiteration of upholding the one - china stand and send a clear signal to the " taiwan independence " forces .
the leader of the taiwan authorities has claimed that " in order to prevent china from using force to encroach upon taiwan , he has unilaterally changed the status quo between the two sides of the strait and has to promote a referendum on the 320 peace . "
this is a slander of the mainland 's efforts for peace and a provocation to cross - strait relations .
at present , the real threat to taiwan 's security does not come from the mainland but from the " taiwan independence " separatist activities carried out vigorously by the taiwan authorities .
the " taiwan independence " separatist forces are the direct sources that undermine the status quo of cross - strait relations and endanger peace in the taiwan strait .
the taiwan authorities distorted the mainland 's opposition to " taiwan independence " separation and the maintenance of stability in the taiwan strait as an excuse for suppressing taiwan 's democracy and freedom and used this as a pretext for holding a referendum .
this is a sheer fabrication and a distortion of right and wrong , in order to gain sympathy and support for them in continuing to carry out their splittist line .
the leader of the taiwan authorities has declared that he will hold a so - called " defense - related referendum " and " peace referendum . " however , whatever it is packaged , such provocative acts can only provoke confrontation and hostility between the two sides of the strait , aggravate tension in cross - strait relations , and push cross - strait relations step by step to the brink of danger .
this runs completely against the mainstream public opinion of the taiwan compatriots in seeking peace , stability , and development , and is not deepening taiwan 's " democracy " but misleading and manipulating the taiwan people and seriously threatening peace and stability in the asia - pacific region . it is bound to meet with universal opposition from the compatriots on both sides of the strait and the international community .
taking a general look at the historical process of the development of the chinese nation , reunification has always been the mainstream and the trend of the times and the desire of the people .
as the motherland becomes stronger day by day , cross - strait cooperation has been strengthened , the international community has universally recognized the pattern of one china has been further consolidated , and any separatist conspiracy is doomed to failure .
