since the september 11 terrorist attacks , the global attention has been focused on security at ports , airports and borders .
as the world 's largest container port to the united states , hong kong undoubtedly responded rapidly to the " port security initiative " put forward by the united states .
in addition , we believe that cutting off the lifeline of terrorist organisations is an effective means to curb terrorist activities .
the daily outflow of funds from the global financial system has made the law enforcement agencies concerned extremely worried about the proceeds of crime and money laundering .
as a major financial centre in asia , we believe that cutting off the funding of terrorists is probably the most effective way to fundamentally tackle the problem of terrorist financing .
at present , hong kong 's legislature is discussing various improvement measures to tighten the existing legislation against terrorist financing , and is actively working in line with international standards and situations , such as the new recommendations of the financial action task force on money laundering ( fatf ) .
we are also working on a better disclosure legislation for reporting suspicious transactions to the parties concerned .
" balance " is also the key to this work : effective investigative powers , protected by constitutional guarantees , individual privacy , and efficiency of the economic and financial systems are all factors that must be considered .
our control measures are based on the rule of law , transparency , fairness and efficiency .
