education is the cornerstone of modern civilization .
to improve the quality of our nationals and increase our comprehensive national strength , we must make great efforts to develop education .
the influence of rural education is extensive , and it has a bearing on the overall situation of rural economic and social development .
since the beginning of reform and opening up , tremendous and profound changes have taken place in china 's urban and rural areas , which are inseparable from the development of education , especially rural education .
the practice of the household contract responsibility system with remuneration linked to output in rural areas has greatly emancipated productive forces .
one of the fundamental reasons why the advanced and practical technologies of agriculture can be popularized on a large scale and township and town enterprises can break out of competition , and the surplus labor force in rural areas can be transferred to coastal areas and towns in large quantities . this is because there are hundreds of millions of rural labor forces that have received compulsory education as the foundation and support , and great achievements have been made in popularizing compulsory education in rural areas .
at present , china 's agriculture and rural economy are in a crucial stage of development . the development of high - quality , high - efficiency , ecological , and security agriculture , the expansion of industrialized agricultural operations , and the shift of surplus labor force in rural areas urgently require an all - round improvement of the quality of rural labor forces .
the rise of the new scientific and technological revolution in the world and the promotion of the comprehensive building of a comfortably well - off society have set still higher demands on the scientific and cultural qualities and ideological and ethical qualities of the vast numbers of rural population .
without the all - round " nine universal " rural areas and the all - round improvement of the peasants ' quality , it will be very difficult to achieve a comfortably well - off standard of living .
we must fully understand the basic , leading , and across - the - board role of rural education in comprehensively building a comfortably well - off society .
