a few days ago , the iraqi interim management committee signed an agreement with the us occupation authorities in baghdad , announcing a timetable for the transfer of power to iraq in a step - by - step manner and by june next year .
the agreement was reluctantly endorsed by the international community : although the eu foreign ministers ' meeting welcomed it , france felt that " the process was too slow " and un secretary general annan , while " encouraged " by the power transfer plan , said that the un role in iraq was " not yet ripe " and russia simply questioned the legality of the agreement .
the iraqi people turned a cold shoulder and the us media even held that " this is a major gamble . "
in short , people are mostly half - hearted and wait - and - see .
the international community has a lot of doubts and misgivings .
this is because people can see that returning to power in iraq is not a move that the united states is willing to accept . therefore , the transfer of power cannot be thorough and is bound to leave many hints .
first of all , the interim government , to be formed in may next year , will not be directly elected by the iraqi people , but will be elected by the " transitional national assembly " elected by the 18 provincial - level election committees .
this is difficult to avoid us control over the legality of the system .
second , the united states has announced that it will not withdraw its forces after the power handover , but instead will turn its original " military occupation " into " military existence . "
the us government announced on 18 november that it has decided to impose quota restrictions on three categories of textiles imported from china : knitting , chest garments , and parking .
at a time when china is making continuous efforts to expand sino - us economic and trade cooperation , the us government 's trade protectionism move cannot but cause deep regret .
as the economic globalization has developed to the present stage , it is extremely inappropriate for the united states to impose new restrictions on chinese textile imports .
first of all , such a move of abuse of the " quota " has restricted the implementation of the wto 's principle of free trade .
on the one hand , he talked in a high - sounding manner about " free trade . " on the other hand , he frequently released " quota " missiles and reerected trade barriers . does this appear to be too arbitrary and fair ?
second , the " limits " have restricted the good momentum of development of sino - us economic and trade relations .
since china and the united states reached agreement in 1999 on china 's accession to the wto , us exports to china have increased by an average of 15 percent a year .
us exports to china from january to september this year increased by 26.2 percent over the same period last year .
in the past two years , us textile raw materials and manufactured goods exports to china have increased by a big margin .
as a matter of fact , china today has become the fastest growing us export to all countries in the world .
there are many reasons why bush 's visit to britain was unable to achieve its purpose . the most important reason was that after the end of the cold war , the united states became the only superpower in the world , and did not keep other people 's eyes on it , and unilateralism has expanded .
the united states , without the authorization of the united nations , launched a war against iraq and disrespected the opinions of its main allies on major international issues , such as the reconstruction of iraq .
according to a recent opinion poll by the european commission , 68 percent of eu citizens think that the reason for the united states to launch a war in iraq is insufficient , and 53 percent believe that the united states poses a threat to world peace .
second , the united states emphasizes anti - terrorism by requiring its allies to provide funding but has no reason to address the issues they are concerned about .
as for the iraqi reconstruction project , the united states is dead at heart , and is unwilling to give a cup to its own companies instead of a major contract awarded for the first tender , while the united states has already decided on steel trade disputes and the world trade organization has imposed high tariffs , and britain 's business circles have expressed the hope that bush 's visit will yield any concessions , but in the end has not made a clear statement .
third , the united states puts its own values above all other countries and insists on carrying out democratic transformation and being criticized . some of its allies demand that the united states respect the culture and characteristics of the islamic countries and believe that one of the reasons for the united states being bogged down in the mire in iraq today is precisely the bitter fruit of its " disrespect " for it .
bush , however , will not change over to new ways because of widespread criticism and opposition . during his visit , he once again defended his iraq policy and emphasized that the us - british coalition forces will continue to use force to deal with violent incidents in iraq .
since bush 's visit to britain has not been realized , the situation in iraq will not develop as the white house hoped .
after six months of debate , the japanese self - defense forces ' advance team eventually headed for iraq by the end of 2003 .
this is the first time that japan has sent troops to an overseas battlefield since the end of world war ii .
it reflects japan 's will to become a political and military power , and also indicates that japan 's defense strategy has begun to change .
the reason why the self - defense force 's visit has attracted people 's attention is that it is not an isolated incident .
taking the opportunity of the afghan war , japan achieved a breakthrough in the self-defense forces going out of its country , adopted the " emergency legislation " on the korean peninsula issue , thus laying down a hint for the self-defense forces to use force or even launch preemptive strikes , and the koizumi cabinet recently adopted the " basic plan to support iraq 's reconstruction , " thereby paving the way for sending troops to iraq .
this step by step has finally broken through the restrictions of japan 's peace constitution and achieved the goal of sending troops overseas .
in addition , japan is also preparing to revise the " concept of basic defense forces " in 2004 in order to legalize and eternal sending of troops overseas , and plans to establish a non-temporary " standing force " abroad .
at the same time , the japanese cabinet meeting , using the so - called " dprk missile threat " as an excuse , made the decision to start deploying a missile defense system in early 2004 and introduced the us - made " standard - 3 " and " patriot - 3 " missiles to intercept missiles outside the atmosphere and return to the atmosphere , thus building a dual missile interception network .
it is not difficult to see that japan 's self-defense forces are developing in the direction of regular armed forces which are " both offensive and defensive " and the so - called " self-defense forces " which are exclusively engaged in defense will exist only in name .
the reason why japan 's action has attracted people 's attention is , first of all , because these military decisions have an impact on japan 's peace constitution .
after visiting the yasukuni shrine , koizumi was interviewed by a japanese reporter and defended his actions .
his arguments were self - contradictory and full of flaws .
asked why koizumi visited the shrine , koizumi replied : " japan 's peace and prosperity were achieved on the basis of those who were sacrificed in the war .
my purpose in visiting the shrine is to pray for peace and prosperity in japan . "
may i ask whether the so - called " war victims " of koizumi include class a war criminals of world war ii such as hideki tojo ?
can we say that japan 's realization of peace and prosperity after the war also has the basis of contributions from class a war criminals ?
a reporter asked why he chose to visit the yasukuni shrine on 1 january .
koizumi said that it was japan 's tradition to pay homage to the shrine on the first day of the new year , and many people went to the shrine on that day .
it is understandable that ordinary people mourned the loss of relatives and friends , and many family members clearly indicated that their visit to the yasukuni shrine was only to commemorate their relatives and friends and to resolutely oppose the worship of class - a war criminals at yasukuni shrine .
the chinese people are reasonable . we have consistently distinguished the japanese people from a small number of militarist elements and separated the ordinary people from rightwing elements . visiting the yasukuni shrine by ordinary people is not the crux of the historical issue .
