from 4 to 6 january , the 12th summit of the south asian union for regional cooperation ( fry ) , which was postponed for a whole year , was held in islamabad . the meeting approved the " south asian free trade framework treaty , " the " south african union protocol additional to the convention on cracking down on terrorism , " the south asian social charter , and other documents , announcing that countries of the south african union will work for common development and cooperation in the economic , cultural , and antiterrorism fields .
during the south african union summit , the bilateral meeting between indian prime minister vajpayee and pakistani president musharraf attracted particular attention .
the handshake between musharraf and vajpayee at the last summit did not enable people to hold too much hopes for the development of bilateral relations .
two years later , as the two sides adopted a series of major measures , such as restoring normal diplomatic relations , building land - air communications , and achieving cease - fire in kashmir , indian - pakistani relations continued to ease up and finally achieved the highest - level meeting on the occasion of the south african union summit .
the two countries have made great progress in the process of improving bilateral relations , and cooperation in the south asian region is ushering in a new turning point .
although indian foreign minister singh said on 4 april that the meeting was a " courtesy " , people believed that the meeting means that indian - pakistani relations will continue to move toward a more positive and pragmatic direction .
the leaders of the two countries have realized that tension and confrontation do not conform to their own interests , but on the contrary have deprived their economic development opportunities one after another .
along with the further development of economic globalization , it has become a pressing task of the two governments to strengthen cooperation and revitalize the economy .
although the result of georgia 's presidential election on 4 april has not yet been officially announced , saakashvili , the candidate jointly nominated by the right - wing political parties and leader of the national movement party , is certain to win .
more than 95 percent of the electorate support saakashvili , the central election commission announced today .
the heads of state of some cis countries also sent congratulatory messages to this young politician .
in fact , saakashvili has already declared his victory as early as the evening of the election ended .
he called this a " victory of the people " and said georgia would take prompt action to open up a new future .
when interviewed by the media , many voters indicated that throwing the ballots to saakashvili means choosing " new hope . "
even former president shevardnadze , who was forced to resign , expressed support for this former political enemy and praised him for " having a young and vigorous spirit and received a good education . "
regarding saakashvili 's hope , people have also noticed that there has been no major change in the situation in georgia over the past two months since shevardnadze resigned .
it can be said that the newly elected president will still face old problems .
the past year has been an important and unusual year in the course of china 's development .
we have waged an arduous struggle against the sudden outbreak of sars and scored major victories at this stage , the economy of our country has maintained a good momentum of development , per capita gdp has exceeded $ 1,000 , crossing a new stage , the successful manned spaceflight of shenzhou v has made the dream of the chinese nation a reality , national unity , social progress , and further improvement of the people 's livelihood .
china 's achievements in various fields have caught the attention of the whole world . the people of the whole country have made tremendous efforts in this regard , displaying courage and strength in defying hardship and danger and in creating miracles .
looking forward to the new year , we are full of confidence and hope .
taking a general view of the domestic and international situations , we are in an important strategic opportunity period that we must firmly grasp and can greatly achieve .
we should persistently take deng xiaoping theory and the important thinking of the " three represents " as the guide , comprehensively implement the spirit of the 16th party congress and the third plenary session of the 16th cpc central committee , conscientiously implement the central authorities ' major guidelines and overall arrangements for this year 's work , and continue to push forward reform , opening up , and modernization .
in doing a good job in this year 's work , we must correctly grasp the situation ; while seeing favorable conditions and new opportunities , we must also be aware of unfavorable conditions and new challenges and enhance our sense of responsibility , urgency , and urgency .
the three - party talks on the iraq issue were held at the un headquarters in new york on the 19 th . un secretary general annan and representatives of the iraqi interim governing council and the us - british provisional management authority held discussions focusing on how the united nations should play its role in the reconstruction of iraq .
the three sides frankly exchanged views on iraq 's political , humanitarian , and security issues and the appointment of the un special representative in iraq .
when the us and britain are faced with the power transfer scheme in iraq being boycotted , it is naturally noteworthy whether or not the united nations will intervene in iraq 's reconstruction .
since the united states announced at the beginning of may last year that the main war in iraq has ended , the situation in iraq has remained turbulent , and attacks against the occupation have continued to break out one after another , with the result that the us - british coalition forces have caused numerous casualties and there have been no peace at all .
former iraqi president saddam was arrested on 13 december last year , but the united states ' joy has not been sustained , the security situation has not taken a turn for the better , and the resistance movement has plunged the occupation authorities into a predicament .
on the other hand , the iraqi people and arab countries unanimously demanded the withdrawal of foreign troops from iraq and the government in iraq so that the iraqi people can manage their own countries .
at the same time , the united states and britain are striving to rebuild the iraqi regime in accordance with their own will and gradually extricate themselves from the mire on this basis in " dignified " fashion .
for this reason , the way and process of handing over power have become the focal point of current iraq affairs .
the power handover plan put forward by the us - british administration and the iraqi provisional governing council in november last year was : the iraqi interim government formed before july 1 this year will be elected by the " transitional national congress . " however , representatives attending the conference will be selected and dispatched by the " provincial - level election committee . "
the shiite faction , which accounts for the majority of the iraqi population , stresses that direct universal suffrage should be held nationwide in order to truly assume power in iraq in a fair and equitable way .
us secretary of state powell 's recent visit to russia remains the focus of public opinion .
on the one hand , this is because the united states and russia play a pivotal role and their mutual relations will have a far - reaching impact on the world today .
more importantly , powell 's moscow visit has substantive contents and has relayed a clear signal : dark clouds have appeared in the sky of russian - us relations .
if these dark clouds were not dispersed in time , the prospects for relations between the two countries would become dim .
although the channels of dialogue between washington and moscow are very open , powell has decided to write an article to explain his stand in the influential russian newspaper , " interest reduction . "
in his article , powell pointed out : the united states is perplexed by a series of incidents in russia 's internal affairs and foreign affairs over the past few months .
he maintained that the russian regime has yet to fully accept the constraints of the law , and the key elements of a civil society , such as freedom of the press and development of political parties , are not solid enough .
russia 's policy in chechnya and its attitude toward neighboring countries of the commonwealth of independent states have made the united states even more worried .
as far as diplomats are concerned , making use of the mass media to make known to the public is the " last resort " in communicating information .
the original intention of the united states in choosing this option gives food for thought , and the russian side feels embarrassed and unhappy about this .
after entering the new century , economic globalization has become a major and serious challenge facing african countries .
the leaders of african countries have come to realize more and more clearly that africa should no longer miss this good opportunity and should rise up to seek countermeasures .
on 9 july 2002 , the african union was formally established and began to operate . since then , african countries on the one hand have actively carried out the " new partnership program for african development , " striven to develop the economy , and tried to extricate themselves from their unfavorable position in economic globalization as soon as possible ; on the other hand , they have exerted great efforts to resolve the major obstacles hindering the great cause of african rejuvenation - - armed conflicts - - - so as to create a united , peaceful , and stable environment .
at present , the overall situation in africa has become more relaxed , hot issues have noticeably lowered , and various countries have enhanced their sense of urgency to end armed conflicts .
with the energetic support of the united nations and the international community , influential regional organizations , regional powers , and noted politicians in africa have taken positive actions and intensified their efforts to resolve regional conflicts and eliminate civil strife . some conflicts and turbulence which have lasted for many years have been basically brought under control .
these include the establishment of a national unity government in the congo ( kinshasa ) last june , the peaceful settlement of a coup crisis in sao paulo and sao paulo in july , the signing of a peace agreement between the liberian government and anti - government armed forces in acra in august , the key talks between the sudanese government and the south anti - government armed forces in september , the holding of peace talks in kenya in october , and the signing of a peace agreement between the burundi government and the burundi government .
of course , the current stable situation in africa is still rather weak , the fruits of peace still need to be consolidated , and some potential or practical armed conflicts remain to be solved .
at the same time , there is still a big gap between the economic growth rate of african countries and the developing countries in asia and other regions , and these are all unfavorable factors in africa 's development .
how the african countries can effectively deal with the challenge of economic globalization and realize their dream of rejuvenation requires the african people to make long - term and arduous efforts .
recently , epidemic outbreaks of high - pathogenic avian flu have occurred one after another in some parts of our country .
the party central committee and the state council attach great importance to this issue , rapidly made a series of major policy decisions , and explicitly put forward the guiding principles , policies , and measures for prevention and treatment work .
all relevant localities and departments have taken emergency actions and gone all out to prevent the spread of the epidemic in accordance with the arrangements of the cpc central committee and the state council .
at present , the work of preventing and controlling bird flu throughout the country is being carried out in a tense and orderly manner .
highly pathogenic avian flu is a type of animal epidemic that spreads fast and causes great harm . it seriously endangers livestock production and seriously endangers the health and safety of the masses .
effectively doing a good job in preventing and controlling the highly pathogenic avian flu has a bearing on the health and safety of the masses , on agricultural development and on increasing peasant incomes , on the overall situation of economic development and social stability . all localities and departments should , under the guidance of the important thinking of " three represents " and in accordance with the requirements of the " law of the people 's republic of china on animal disease prevention , " strengthen leadership , coordinate closely , rely on science , and strictly prevent and deal with the masses .
as the world 's largest debtor , the amount of us foreign debts is also increasing .
the total debts owed by foreign creditors amounted to 6.494 trillion u.s. dollars by the end of september , an increase of 2.2 percent over the previous year , the u.s. treasury department reported today .
on average , each american is in debt of over $ 20,000 .
coincidentally , a research report released by the international monetary fund this week sharply sounded the alarm for the ever - shaking financial foundation of the united states , pointing out that the continually breaking record in us foreign debts has reached a level threatening global financial stability .
statistics show that foreign private investors have controlled about 40 percent of the us government bonds .
this inevitably makes one think of the tricks president roosevelt took in the first half of the 20 th century : adopting a deficit policy to stimulate the economy , and resolving the problem of fiscal deficits through external debt .
this move indeed played an important role in stimulating " effective demand " to resolve urgent economic crisis .
however , people can see that many us administrations tend to regard this as a " panacea . "
however , since president reagan initiated a tax cut and expansion in the 1980 's , the united states ' financial deficit has gradually increased and has eventually become the biggest debtor nation .
the convening of the first round of the six - party talks is an important step in the process of peacefully resolving the nuclear issue on the korean peninsula .
some common points that the various parties formed in this round of talks have laid the necessary foundation for the continued talks and further cleared up the objectives , approaches , and principles for resolving the korean peninsula nuclear issue .
over the past few months , all parties concerned have persisted in peacefully resolving the nuclear issue on the peninsula through dialogue , and on the basis of the results of the first round of six - party talks , extensively conducted coordination and consultations at various levels , and made unremitting efforts to hold the second round of talks as soon as possible .
at the same time , the dprk and the united states have further demonstrated varying degrees of flexibility .
now major progress has been made in the preparatory work for the talks , and a good talk is popular support .
what achievements the second round of six - party talks can achieve and whether the peace talks can be maintained are of general concern to the parties concerned and the international community .
commenting on the issue , a chinese foreign ministry spokesman said : the goal of the six - party talks is to maintain and promote the process of a peaceful settlement of the issue through dialogue . we are willing to make joint efforts with all parties concerned in this regard .
china 's basic starting point is to maintain peace and stability on the korean peninsula and realize a non - nuclear peninsula .
the chinese side holds that so long as all parties concerned adhere to the sincerity of peace talks , respect each other , and hold consultations on an equal footing , they will be able to create favorable conditions for promoting the settlement of relevant issues .
in the late 1970 s , murray relations deteriorated and the two countries severed diplomatic ties in 1981 .
us president reagan listed a long series of crimes for libyan leader qadhafi , such as accusing libya of secretly developing nuclear weapons , and engaging in foreign military intervention and terrorism .
from a battle of words to a fight between the two sides , the united states and libya launched two surgical strikes on the " prairie fire " and the " golden valley . "
since then , the united states has imposed economic sanctions against libya , struck political blows , contained diplomatic moves , and threatened the military .
qadhafi , under heavy pressure , did not yield .
right now , the warming - up of murray relations is entirely due to the deterrent effect of the iraq war , which seems to be biased .
as a matter of fact , qadhafi , with a unique character , has for many years been fighting the united states while at the same time he has always thrown an olive branch into the united states , but unfortunately he has not received any response .
after the iraq war ended , all sides in the middle east adjusted their strategies and regional forces and created an opportunity for the resumption of murray building .
as far as qadhafi is concerned , repairing relations with the united states can end sanctions , revitalize the economy , improve people 's livelihood , extricate itself from an isolated position , and merge into the international community .
it is beneficial to give up those things that have not yet been and cannot be found for the time being , and to exchange for a new environment of dense willow trees and bright flowers .
from 7 to 8 february , important political figures from europe and the united states and other regions in the world gathered in munich , germany , to attend the 40 th munich security policy conference .
the so - called " munich security policy conference " is an international security forum founded by unofficial personages in germany and funded by the german government . in recent years , especially after the " 9.11 " , people have increasingly attached importance to the forum , which is known as the " davos forum " in the field of security .
an important item on the agenda of this meeting is transatlantic relations .
the remarks made by the european and american political leaders at the meeting show that both sides are making every effort to cast off the shadow of the iraq war on bilateral relations and to return to the track of cooperation .
bertrham , director of the berlin institute for international and security affairs , said that this was a meeting for the restoration of european - american relations , and that both sides had the desire to get close again .
as far as eu - us relations are concerned , the new information that comes out of the meeting is that europe and the united states need to resume dialogue ; it needs to seriously consider the common tasks facing both sides , and to find the interests needed to fulfill these common tasks .
compared with last year 's meeting , the smell of gunpowder in this year 's meeting has disappeared and the stances of the two sides are getting closer .
although the " old europe " represented by france and germany still brokered in the mind of the united states in launching the iraq war , they said they would " look forward to the next . "
german foreign minister fischer said at the meeting : " although we have different views on the war , we must work together to ensure peace in the post - war iraq . we must look ahead to this .
although germany will not send troops to iraq , germany will not obstruct nato from playing a direct role in iraq , he added .
the united states , which has won the upper hand in the modern media field , monopolized a large portion of the right to speak of international news . the antennae of its media have long been spread all over the world and have simply reached an all - pervasive extent . why is it that it still has to spend a huge sum of money to set up a satellite television station specially covering 22 countries in the middle east ?
in the words of a responsible person of the " freedom 1 " television station , it is necessary to provide arab countries with a " comprehensive and just " news platform .
some analysts pointed out , however , that the " free no . 1 " policy will be a strategic weapon of the united states in carrying out public opinion infiltration , cultural intrusion , and suppression of plots against arab countries . it will be an important propaganda tool for the united states to pursue its policy of integrating the middle east with the islamic world .
as matters stand , the mission of " freedom no . 1 " is extraordinary , and there are three major choices : first , it spreads the " concept of freedom . "
the united states believes that islamic civilization is a serious obstacle to the promotion of modern civilization in the west . the extremist religious forces in the middle east are a hotbed for international terrorism mainly characterized by anti-us forces . in order to effectively fight against terrorism , it is imperative to remold the islamic world and enable it to identify and accept the western value concepts , lifestyles , and political systems .
the united states is trying to instill its own ideology into the arab people through the imperatives of the " free no. 1 " program .
second , it will improve the image of the united states .
the united states practices unilateralism and acts perversely on its own in dealing with a series of international issues , thus forcing arab and islamic countries and their counterparts in the world to do what they want to do .
after the " 9.11 " incident , the contradictions between the united states , which has consistently been partial to israel , and the islamic world in the middle east have intensified .
without conclusive evidence and un authorization , the united states invaded and occupied iraq by force in the name of eliminating weapons of mass destruction and counter - terrorism , arousing strong resentment among muslim people .
pakistan and india held talks in islamabad from february 16 to 18 , with the hope for peace again rising on the south asian subcontinent .
officials of the two countries have decided on the agenda and model for future talks and established a mechanism for sustained dialogue . this marks the resumption of the process of dialogue between pakistan and india after being broken off for two years , which has laid a foundation for the two countries to gradually resolve all outstanding issues , including the kashmir dispute , and demonstrates the valuable sincerity of both sides for peace .
prior to the talks , although a series of goodwill moves taken by the two sides prior to the talks showed that the relations between the two countries were full of warmth , analysts still mostly held a cautious attitude toward the prospects for the peace process .
it is no wonder that looking back at the sudden ups and downs in the relations between pakistan and india in recent years , it seems that no one dare guarantee : today , the sunlight on the negotiating table will not turn into a lightning on the border tomorrow .
on the 18th , however , the smiling pakistani state secretary for foreign affairs , mohammad hohar ayub , read the two countries ' statement , which gave an impetus to the two countries ' optimistic feelings . this made the eyes of many people who had long been concerned about the situation in south asia brightened up .
first of all , the timetable set for the talks is highly operable . the two sides not only specified the specific time and topics for the talks but also set different levels of talks according to the degree of importance of the topics .
second , the two sides have drawn a lesson from the failure of the leaders of the two countries in conducting direct dialogue during the meeting in july 2001 , and adopted a " step - by - step " approach of dialogue to ensure that the talks will proceed from a low level and be fully prepared for high - level dialogue .
third , after experiencing several bilateral relations , the two countries unanimously agreed that war is not a good way to resolve disputes , and both sides should stay far away from war . this consensus has laid a foundation for the leaders of the two countries to reach an understanding that " pakistan and india will never go to war again . "
to comprehensively and accurately understand and implement the " one country , two systems " policy , we must integrate " one country " with " two systems , " " patriotism " with " love for hong kong , " integrate the respect for hong kong 's high degree of autonomy with the maintenance of state sovereignty , and integrate the maintenance of hong kong 's capitalism with the adherence to the socialist main body of the country .
only in this way will it be possible to safeguard the well - being of the hong kong compatriots in real earnest and to accord with the long - term interests of the country and the entire people .
since hong kong 's return to the motherland , the central government has unswervingly implemented the principle of " one country , two systems " and acted in strict accordance with the basic law .
the vast number of hong kong compatriots enjoy unprecedented democratic rights in their status as masters of the country .
with the vigorous support of the central government and the hinterland of the motherland , hong kong has overcome various risks and challenges such as the impact of the asian financial crisis and continued to maintain its status as an international financial , trade , and shipping center .
practice has proven that the principle of " one country , two systems " has great vitality .
the purpose of republishing comrade deng xiaoping 's speech 20 years ago has once again proclaimed to the world the firm determination of the central authorities to implement the principle of " one country , two systems , " and it is all the more to let people understand the principle of " one country , two systems " comprehensively and accurately and constantly push forward the great practice of " one country , two systems . "
the party central committee and the state council held a grand national science and technology award meeting here today .
president hu jintao presented awards to academician liu dongsheng and academician wang yongzhi , who won the 2003 top national science and technology prize .
the conference presented awards to scientists and technicians who won the national award for scientific and technological progress and the " chinese manned spaceflight project " and the 2003 national natural science award , the national technological invention award , and the national scientific and technological progress award .
on behalf of the party central committee and the state council , i would like to extend warm congratulations to all the award winners !
i would like to extend my sincere greetings and high respect to science and technology personnel on all fronts of the country !
for our country , the first 20 years of this century are an important strategic opportunity period that we must firmly grasp and achieve success .
we must concentrate our efforts on building a better - off society that benefits a higher - level population of over 1 billion people in an all - round way .
we must put the development of science and technology in a more important and prominent position by making the best use of this strategic opportunity period and striving to do something .
after the " 9.11 " incident , us president bush dished out a " preemptive " strategy in june 2002 , putting it into practice in us foreign relations , and launched the first " preemptive " war in iraq in march last year .
the idea of " preemptive " not only runs counter to the norms of international law with " mutual respect for sovereignty and territorial integrity " as its core , but is also bound to give rise to the dangerous effect of following the example . a new turbulent situation will arise in the international order because of this .
at the beginning of the introduction of the " preemptive " theory , some us political leaders raised the following question : " what should other countries do if they follow the example one after another ? "
as a result , over the past two years , more and more countries claimed to be " preemptive " and more " preemptive " efforts have been made .
this is a new trend worthy of attention and study .
in the same month , australian prime minister howard stepped forward to express support for bush 's " preemptive " strategy .
he said that australia would adopt a " preemptive " strategy if terrorists were to attack australia , and would not hesitate to take military actions against surrounding countries .
he even proposed incorporating the principle of " preemptive strikes " into the un charter , saying that it is necessary to amend the un charter and give various countries the " preemptive " rights in order to strike at terrorists or countries that support terrorist activities .
in the northeast asian region , japan 's defense agency pointed out in its " defense white paper " published as early as july 1999 that japan could launch a " preemptive " strike on foreign bases before facing missile attacks or military invasion .
after the iraq war , the clamor in japan for a " preemptive " strategy was even more rampant .
recently , international opinion has commented on the current us africa policy .
the " foreign policy focus of the united states " published in january this year , entitled " prospects of africa 's policy in 2004 . the article holds that in the past year , the bush administration 's foreign policy has directly or indirectly exerted a negative impact on africa . in particular , due to the united states ' all - out concern over the war against terrorism and the proliferation of weapons of mass destruction , especially the lack of skill for the united states to divide in iraq , it has already greatly scattered its concern about africa .
people still remember that in order to show concern for africa , the bush administration formulated the " president 's emergency plan for treating aids " in january last year and promised to provide africa with at least $ 3 - billion of funds each year .
in july last year , president bush visited senegal , south africa , botswana , uganda , and nigeria , promising to provide $ 15 - billion to african countries in aids prevention and treatment , and $ 100 - million to use against african terrorist activities , and announced the food emergency relief programs and educational assistance programs .
these aid programs were once welcomed by african countries and won praise internationally .
one year has passed , however , the concrete actions taken by the united states are delayed in implementing them .
africa is in urgent need of assistance .
after entering the new century , africa is facing various development challenges . in order to achieve the united nations ' " development goals for the century " formulated in 2000 , work hard to reduce hunger and poverty , promote health and education , africa set up an " african union " to coordinate all of the affairs of the continent , and formulated a " new partnership plan for african development " aimed at promoting the development of various countries . however , due to its weak economic foundation , development funds have always been very short .
the united nations has repeatedly called on developed countries to use 0.7 percent of their gross domestic product for official aid to the least developed countries .
however , official aid accounted for only 0.1 percent of the gross domestic product , far short of the united nations ' demand , and ranked last in the list of donor countries .
recently , european public opinion has been discussing whether the meeting of the " three magnates " -- german chancellor gerhard schroeder , french president jacques chirac , and british prime minister blair -- is gradually moving toward a mechanism .
the media called the " three magnates " of germany and britain the " new three troika " of the eu , and the relationship among the three countries is called the " new triangle . "
the " new triangle " is a new thing , and no matter which direction it will go and what angle it will observe , generally speaking , this " new triangle " seems to be favorable to europe 's integration process , and will help europe play an important role on the international stage as a pole in a multipolar world .
taking a general look at the history of europe over the past 100 years , a basic characteristic of the german - british triangular relationship is that britain and britain join hands , restrain , or resist germany .
the two world wars proved this .
during the cold war , east germany and west germany were muddled in china 's warsaw pact and nato .
after the end of the cold war , germany became stronger after reunification , and the pattern of forces in west europe was unbalanced . france became more suspicious , causing the " axis of germany " to go out of order for a time , bringing britain and britain closer again , and its intention was still to contain germany .
however , in recent years , with the reopening of the " germany - france axis " and the fierce collision between the world 's unipolar and multipolar concepts , inside the eu has been bogged down in a serious split on the iraq issue ;
the " old europe " represented by germany and france is completely contrary to the stand of the " new europe " represented by britain and poland on the iraq war issue .
this round of split happened to be the largest in history by the eu .
egyptian president hosni mubarak has criticized the adoption of a single reform model in arab countries in cairo , in an interview with xinhua , warning that such an attempt is just the opposite of what it wishes for the security and stability of the middle east .
he held that reform measures should be based on their own characteristics , act according to their capability , and the unitary reform model should neglect the cultural background , social customs , and religious characteristics of different countries .
at the same time , he pointed out that arab countries welcome foreign aid in the process of reform , but such efforts should be made to recognize the different national conditions and respect the wishes of various countries , so as to promote the political , economic , and cultural reforms of arab countries .
the egyptian leaders ' remarks represented the common view of arab countries .
at present , under the pressure of anti-terrorism , antiproliferation , and democratic reform , the middle east , as one of the hot spots in the world , is brewing new turbulence and will lead to new integration .
after going through two wars in afghanistan and iraq , how should iraq carry out political reconstruction , which was once considered one of the " axis of evil " by the united states ?
how will various political and social systems in the middle east change ?
this is not only a concern of the arab world and the international community , but also of interest to the united states and its western allies .
after meeting with visiting bahrain crown prince sahman in washington on 9 april , us secretary of state colin powell reiterated that the united states would pursue a " western - style democratic and capitalist program " in iraq and the middle east .
he also stressed : " we are considering what we can do and how we can institutionalize this . "
last year was a " cultural and educational year " designated by the international olympic committee .
the beijing organizing committee for the games took advantage of this opportunity to hold a series of educational activities to disseminate advanced culture and popularize olympic knowledge .
among them , the publication of the " reader on olympic knowledge for secondary school students " , mainly for young people , is a very important achievement .
the reader is both energetic and colorful . it mainly uses the method of telling stories to vividly introduce the knowledge of olympic sports and the essence of the olympic spirit . it is a good textbook that helps teenagers and students enhance their understanding of olympic sports and helps raise their enthusiasm for social participation in the olympics .
last year , the beijing organizing committee for the olympic games specially designed a class program with the logo for teenage students .
the concept of " green olympics " is to prepare for and host the olympics with such ideas of sustainable development as protecting the environment and protecting the ecological balance .
we hope that these class statements will standardize the conduct of young students as required by the class and gradually make them a qualified practitioner and promoter of the concept of " green olympics . "
education is one of the core contents of the olympic movement and also an important embodiment of the " olympics of humanity . "
the true purpose of the olympic games is to educate young people from a new angle and use a new method to promote the harmonious physical and mental development of young people , thereby contributing toward the establishment of a peaceful and beautiful world .
therefore , the combination of physical education and education has not only opened up a new vista for the development of education but also made the olympic games more educational .
the " green olympics " is one of the three major concepts for beijing to host the 2008 olympics .
the core contents are to greatly improve the environmental quality of the capital , create a beautiful environment for the olympic games , and build an ecological city .
to this end , it is necessary to extensively adopt environmental protection technology and means , promote environmental management , urban and rural greening and beautification , and the development of environmental protection industries on a large scale , constantly enhance the entire society 's awareness of environmental protection , and encourage the public to actively participate in various activities to improve the ecological environment .
doing a good job in implementing the " green olympics " is an important task for us to implement the idea of " people first " put forward by the third plenary session of the 16th cpc central committee , establish a comprehensive , coordinated , and sustainable scientific development concept , and promote the comprehensive , coordinated , and sustainable economic and social development of beijing municipality .
we must attach great importance to this issue .
to achieve the goal of the green olympics , beijing municipality has drawn up an " action plan for the olympic games " and a " ecological and environmental protection plan " on the basis of the " 10th five - year plan " and the " report on the bid to host the olympic games , " thus formulating new goals and plans for environmental construction and protection in the next few years .
it will be carried out in a planned and step - by - step way to comprehensively realize the goal of hosting the green olympics .
on 25 february , the us state department published the " 2003 country reports on human rights practices , " which once again criticized more than 190 countries and regions for their human rights conditions , saying that the human rights situation in many countries , including china , was not good enough to meet us standards , and that some other countries suffered retrogression in the key area of human rights .
of course , there are still countries with tremendous improvement in the human rights situation , such as afghanistan and iraq , but this is the " credit " to the us armed forces in overthrowing the former regime and " liberating " the two countries .
as for the human rights situation in the united states ?
as in previous years , the report was reluctant to talk about anything like gold .
on 1 march , the information office of the state council issued the " us human rights record in 2003 , " making up for the deficiencies in the us human rights report .
the article , based on a host of facts , introduces the human rights problems in the united states and the united states ' human rights violations against other countries .
the americans have a tradition of stressing honesty and trustworthiness and have the tradition of making mistakes .
as everyone knows , the story of george washington cutting the cherry tree when he was little is a vivid example .
now that the united states has become the sole superpower in the world , it does not speak the truth .
recently , reports by japan 's mainstream media on china 's economic development have changed quietly .
contrary to the " china threat theory " in the past , many reports in japan have begun to believe that china 's economic development has promoted the recovery of the japanese economy , and the vigorous demand for the chinese market has become an important driving force for japan 's economic development .
the us newsweek recently also carried an article saying that the rise of china is an opportunity and not a threat to other countries , especially neighboring countries .
the widely circulated " china threat theory " is being replaced by " china opportunity theory . "
the " china threat theory " maintains that china 's development will pose a threat to other countries , especially its neighbors .
however , this statement , which was meant to provoke , was not accepted by china 's neighbors .
former malaysian prime minister mahathir once said bluntly , " asian countries need not fear china 's growing military and economic strength because china has no tradition of conquering foreign countries . "
in a long - range plan published by the indian defense ministry , it also holds that china does not pose a military threat to india .
in the economic and trade field , governments and enterprises of all countries have regarded china as the best choice in expanding their markets . overseas investors with strategic insight have resolutely written down the " china opportunity theory " with their actions : of the world 's top 500 enterprises , over 400 have come to invest in china .
for several years in a row , china has ranked first in the world in attracting foreign capital .
gp is an important macroeconomic indicator of the world .
it is of utmost importance to maintain gay growth in the entire process of china 's modernization .
we must maintain the momentum of rapid economic growth just one percentage point increase of the present level of gp in our country .
to a large extent , the great goal of building a comfortably well - off society and the realization of the third - step strategic objective of modernization have to depend on the sustained and rapid growth of gp .
however , we should also see that there are also shortcomings in gay standards .
for instance , it is not easy to accurately reflect the quality and structure of economic growth , it is not easy to reflect the social welfare level actually enjoyed by the people , nor can it accurately assess social distribution and social justice .
on the other hand , ginger is not the only one .
in our assessment of achievements , we should not merely look at the growth of gp ; we should also look at the reality of the material and cultural life of the masses , and see to it that the employment situation , social security , and even social justice , social order , social management , social harmony , and so on are all determined .
therefore , we must treat the existing gp accounting system with a scientific spirit , a scientific attitude , and a scientific ideological method , and put gasim in a position of overall economic and social development .
we should maintain a certain growth rate , yet we should not regard it too seriously , still less should we unilaterally and painstakingly pursue it .
since the un security council delegation visited six western african countries at the end of june last year , the overall situation in the region has undergone encouraging changes although there has been some time or so in some individual countries .
we are pleased to note that the sierra leone government is making positive progress in enhancing its military and police capabilities and in strengthening its control of diamonds and preparing for local government elections . the unmik is also gradually reducing its size according to its established plan .
what is equally gratifying is that with the deployment of the unmik , liberia is gradually shaking off the influence of protracted war and is beginning to embark on the road of recovery and reconstruction .
guinea bissau has made positive progress in its political process and has promised to hold legislative elections in march this year .
the peace process in cote d'ivoire has again taken a turn for the better after suffering a number of setbacks . all sides have promised to implement the " lee - na - malcolm agreement " and the " new army " 's declaration on returning to the government of national reconciliation . the security council is studying the issue of sending peacekeeping troops to cote d'ivoire .
we hope that the un security council will make a decision on this issue as soon as possible .
the secretariat , the west african economic community , and the parties concerned have also worked hard from the regional perspective to resolve cross - border issues such as small arms , mercenary troops , and children , and have achieved positive results .
when fully affirming the above progress , we should see that the overall situation in west africa is still fragile . in particular , due to geographical and historical reasons , various countries in this region maintain close ties and affect each other 's situation . turbulence in a country often affects neighboring countries or even the entire region .
therefore , just as the security council report recommended , the international community , including the security council , must adhere to a comprehensive and comprehensive strategy and make great efforts to resolve the cross - border issue . at the same time , it should actively assist relevant countries and regional and sub - regional organizations such as the african union and west africa economic zones to strengthen their ability to prevent and resolve conflicts .
we have a common understanding that children are the future of the world .
we have the obligation to create the best and most appropriate conditions for them to live and study so as to facilitate their growth , maturity and success .
it is regrettable , however , that tens of thousands of children are still harmed by armed conflicts in the contemporary world .
what they have experienced are turmoil and backwardness , and what they see is violence and sabotage , harm and abuse , and sorrow and helplessness .
therefore , it is an important duty of the international community to protect children from being harmed by armed conflicts .
all countries , especially the parties concerned in the conflicts , should make the greatest efforts in this regard .
we are pleased to see that in recent years the united nations has adopted a series of measures to promote the protection of children in armed conflicts , and have achieved positive results .
the security council successively adopted four resolutions , namely , 1261 ( 1999 ) , 1314 ( 2000 ) , 1379 ( 2001 ) , and 1460 ( 2003 ) , providing an important framework for the work of protecting children .
the peacekeeping activities deployed by the united nations in some regions take the protection of children as an important task , including the appointment of child protection advisers . in the process of helping the countries to be stationed there to carry out plans for disarming , recovering , and returning to the society , special needs of the children were fully taken into consideration .
some peace agreements promoted or participated in by the united nations also include provisions on the protection of children .
national reconciliation is an important condition for the establishment of lasting peace and stability in the region after the conflict .
if the parties concerned cannot bury the old grudges after the conflict ended , it will be difficult to really consolidate the peace situation and the flames of the conflict may even be ignited again .
in many cases , the realization of national reconciliation after the conflicts requires the joint efforts of the parties concerned and , at the same time , also requires the support and assistance of the international community , especially the united nations .
over the years , the united nations has played a useful role in helping promote national reconciliation , and has accumulated a lot of experiences in this regard . in our opinion , to successfully help countries achieve national reconciliation after conflicts , the united nations must properly handle the following three major relationships :
it is necessary to take into consideration the relationship between short - term needs and long - term objectives .
national reconciliation usually takes a certain process , and it is very difficult to achieve it overnight .
there should be different focuses at different stages .
to promote national reconciliation , it is first necessary to let former combat personnel " bid farewell to weapons " and create a safe environment .
during this stage , it is very important to strive to enable former combat personnel to discharge their armed forces , resume their duties , and return to society .
we are pleased to see that the situation in bosnia - herzegovina has become increasingly stable , relations among various nationalities have further relaxed , initial results have been achieved in economic reconstruction , and the work of returning refugees has been basically completed , and relations with neighboring countries have been improving day by day .
the progress made in the peace process in bosnia - herzegovina has not come easily and is gratifying .
we wish to extend congratulations to the government and people of bosnia - herzegovina , and sincerely hope that all sides in bosnia - herzegovina will continue to make efforts to further strengthen mutual trust and cooperation and constantly push forward the peace process .
at the same time , we have also noticed that the state - level institutions and capacity building in bosnia - herzegovina still need to be further improved , and in particular , reforms in the judicial and police fields still face challenges .
we believe that it is appropriate for the high - ranking representatives to regard this as their priority in their work in the first half of this year , and we support the efforts of the bosnian government to actively coordinate with the work of the high - ranking representatives .
it is believed that with the help of the international community , the people of bosnia - herzegovina will continue to score new achievements in building their country , embark on the road of self - determination and development at an early date , and achieve the goal of merging themselves into europe .
the peace and stability of bosnia and herzegovina are of great significance for the realization of lasting peace and development in the region .
the chinese side has always been concerned about the development of the situation in bosnia - herzegovina , and will , together with the international community , continue to make its due contribution to helping bosnia - herzegovina achieve lasting peace and stability and economic development .
china appreciates the efforts made by the counter - terrorism commission to promote the implementation of resolution 1373 ( 2001 ) by various countries , to help strengthen the building of the capacity of developing countries for fighting against terrorism , and to support the committee in strengthening coordination and cooperation with relevant international , regional , and sub - regional organizations in the struggle against terrorism .
at the same time , we hope that the counter - terrorism committee will increase its efforts in providing anti - terrorism assistance and strive to meet the actual needs of developing countries .
at present , the issue of the anti - terrorism committee has aroused the concern of the vast number of member states .
after repeated consultations , the anti - terrorism committee submitted a formal report and distributed it as a security council document .
after more than two years of practice , the existing structure and mode of operation of the counter - terrorism committee have truly revealed shortcomings , such as too heavy a report burden on member states , too many meetings and documents , the need to improve the work results , and insufficient coordination among experts .
therefore , we fully support the necessary reforms of the counter - terrorism commission , and we agree with the package of proposals put forward in the report , such as the establishment of an anti - terrorism committee , and we hope to resolve the existing problems as soon as possible , particularly the issue of the heavy burden on the report of the member states .
i would like to stress here that revitalization and reform is a continuous process , no matter how reform is carried out , the committee on anti - terrorism should maintain policy guidance and guidance , and any policy decision should be made through consultation at the plenary session of the anti - terrorism committee .
in recent years , the issue of small arms has been closely followed by the international community .
this shows that all sides are increasingly aware of the harm caused by the excessive accumulation and illegal trafficking of small weapons to the stability of the regions and countries concerned , the post - war reconstruction of the country , and social development .
it is fortunate that the united nations has taken a series of effective actions to solve this problem .
in 2001 , the " protocol on guns " attached to the " un convention against transnational organized crime " and the " program of action " of the un small arms were successively reached .
this has provided a legal and policy basis for the proper resolution of the small arms issue , and has demonstrated the determination of the international community to crack down on the illegal trade of small arms .
in the past three years , the international community has made great progress in promoting the effective implementation of the " gun protocol " and the implementation of the " program of action . " in particular , the successful convening of the first annual meeting of the united nations in 2003 has provided new impetus for the continued comprehensive and effective implementation of the " program of action . "
the resolution no . 58 / 241 adopted by the current session of the general assembly decided to set up a working group to negotiate for the identification and tracing of an international document on the illegal use of small arms , which will undoubtedly further promote efforts by the international community to crack down on the illegal trade of small arms .
likewise , the security council has also paid increasingly great attention to the issue of small arms . it has held special deliberations several times and adopted the chairman 's statement and resolution .
moreover , when reviewing a series of issues on protecting civilians , women , and children in conflicts , the security council stressed the importance of dealing with the issue of small arms .
developing the economy and eliminating poverty are the basic premise for achieving sustainable development .
sustainable economic development is the material foundation for environmental protection and all - round social progress .
without resolving the issue of survival , there will be no development , let alone sustainable development .
promoting economic development and working hard to eliminate poverty is the only way for developing countries to move toward sustainable development .
without solving the problem of poverty for the developing countries , the development of the developed countries can hardly sustain .
rational utilization of resources and protection of the environment are the inevitable demands of achieving sustainable development .
development is impossible to proceed at the cost of wasting resources and sacrificing the environment .
natural resources are not inexhaustible and inexhaustible , but the demand for the development of human society is steadily growing . if relations between the two sides are not properly handled , this will inevitably worsen the ecological environment and seriously threaten the survival and development of mankind .
only by following the path of a recycling economy based on the most effective use of resources and the protection of the environment can sustainable development be achieved .
achieving comprehensive social progress and improving the people 's living standards and quality is the ultimate goal of sustainable development .
