china takes measures to prevent foot - and - mouth disease from entering tajikistan
xinhua news agency , beijing , january 15 ( reporter du yu ) the ministry of agriculture and the state general administration of quality supervision , inspection , and quarantine jointly issued a notice the other day , prohibiting the import of cloven - hoofed animals and their products from tajikistan directly or indirectly , and those that have arrived at china 's ports are returned or destroyed .
three cases of foot - and - mouth disease have been reported in tajikistan recently , according to a report from the world organization for animal health ( oie ) .
in order to protect the safety of china 's livestock industry , the ministry of agriculture and the state general administration of quality supervision , inspection , and quarantine also issued a notice banning mail , or tourist from bringing cloven - hoofed animals and their products into the country .
once discovered , they shall be returned or destroyed without exception .
transport vehicles such as international navigation ships , airplanes , trains , and so on passing through china or staying in china must be sealed up if birds and their products are found to have come from korea , and waste matter , scane , and so on must be handled without harm under the supervision of the entry - exit inspection and quarantine organization and shall not be discarded without authorization .
the notice demands that the smuggled cloven - hoofed animals and their products intercepted by the customs and border defense departments shall be destroyed without exception under the supervision of the entry - exit inspection and quarantine organization .
