how should beijing look at the pan - blue forces that may form a new ruling party ?
first of all , we should understand that the pan - blue army , which may take power again , is no longer simply the dominance of the kuomintang , but the convergence of the blue army and the convergence of internal traditions with the local factions .
at present , close cooperation during the election period cannot be regarded as an inevitable relationship in the future .
if he is expected to win the election , he is bound to need considerable time for internal integration . the coming election of the legislative yuan at the end of this year will also make it very difficult for the lien - soong regime to make a major change in cross - strait relations .
unless it is aware that the improvement of cross - strait relations can add points to taiwan 's internal politics and be sure to make achievements in a short period of time , the most important thing is to let the people feel this achievement .
based on this background , beijing should temporarily postpone the move to promote reunification and allow lien and soong to consolidate the internal situation of the " traditional blue camp " leaders .
more than half a century has passed since the first nuclear explosion in new mexico by the united states in july 1945 and the attack on japan in august of the same year .
although the arms race between the two superpowers in the united states and the soviet union has caused the accumulation of nuclear weapons to collapse of the entire world , both sides unfortunately realized the danger of nuclear war and avoided pushing the button for nuclear war .
after the disintegration of the soviet union and the world entered the post - cold war era , the danger of a large - scale nuclear war has basically been eliminated .
at the same time , however , the danger of nuclear proliferation has increased instead of decreasing .
this proliferation phenomenon is reflected in two aspects .
first , proceeding from the objective of regional hegemony , confrontation with neighboring countries , safeguarding security , or pursuing blackmail , certain countries with considerable resources and strength strive to produce and possess nuclear weapons by various means .
the other is the collective organizations of some non - state countries , especially muslim extremist forces that harbor a strong hatred of the western world , and they are also doing everything possible to look for small nuclear weapons , at the expense of harming a large number of innocent people , and carrying out bloody terrorist activities against the west .
under such demand , intermediaries engaged in the transfer and sale and sale of nuclear weapons and related technology and the " black market of nuclear weapons " have emerged as the times require . moreover , the scale of such sales has increasingly expanded and has become an important component part of the current world nuclear proliferation .
as a descendant of the yan emperor of china in the hangzhou - jiahu region , the image of the countryside south of the chang jiang and the life of farmers in the old times remained in my memory today .
after returning to their homeland after other years , they found that in the green field along the shanghai - hangzhou expressway , there were only three floors of houses built by the peasants , but very few people were working on the ground .
this really surprised me . it is difficult for me to believe that such great changes will take place in my own land , which still has a deep affection for my people in a foreign country .
however , we cannot help feeling surprised and shocked when we saw on the internet some reports on on on - the - spot investigation of china 's rural conditions .
unexpectedly , the dark side that could not be imagined still exists in china 's rural areas , and the chinese peasants still led a life of humiliation and hardship .
after their on - the - spot interviews in the rural areas of anhui , henan , and hebei , chen guidi and his wife delivered a long report entitled " investigation of china 's rural areas . " they asked for lives for the peasants , which shocked the chinese society .
from the large number of facts that the peasants were corrupted by corrupt officials and suppressed and even killed innocent people , they came to the following conclusion : " when we approached the chinese peasants , we felt unprecedentedly shocked and hidden pain . we saw the unimaginable sin that you could not imagine , could not have imagined it , could not have the resistance , could not imagine it , could not have been silent , and could not imagine it . "
this really makes people feel weeping at the heart of their hearts .
malaysia 's prime minister abdullah al - abdullah al - abdullah al - abdullah al - abdullah al - salem announced his dissolution of the parliament wednesday and the general election will be held in the near future .
the election will be a significant event in his political career and will be of symbolic significance to malaysia 's political situation and its development trend , he said .
al - hussein , who took over the leadership from mahathir in november last year , has been in office for only four months .
in spite of this , he still decided to dissolve the parliament and hold an early general election .
there are at least two meanings : first , abdullah expressed satisfaction with his four - month administration performance and full confidence in his intention to vote , and second , he hoped to consolidate his power base through this means so that he could walk out of the shadow of mahathir .
undoubtedly , the decision made by abdullah al - la reflects that he has made a comprehensive assessment of the domestic political situation .
malaysia 's current economic situation is good , and there is no question of being exploited by the opposition parties .
what is more , since duan took office , he has adopted some highly visibility measures in fighting corruption , including the arrest and prosecution of former land and cooperative development minister garakan [ name as transliterated ] on charges of corruption . this has also enabled the public to be optimistic about future anticorruption actions .
at the same time , he called for improved civil service efficiency , which is also an encouraging move .
since its birth , the eu 's growth and formalization has been strongly influenced by france 's politics and culture .
diplomatic efforts should be made to gain independence and autonomy , and the attitude and method of handling world affairs should be different from that of the united states . this is the direction of the eu 's foreign policy . from this we can clearly see the shadow of france .
it is precisely for this reason that the international community , including china , russia , and arab countries , hopes to see the rise of the eu and see a completely independent force in international exchanges .
it must be admitted that since the end of the 1980 s , the eu has indeed been working toward this direction in the diplomatic field .
in december 1992 , the heads of eu countries unanimously agreed at the macedonian summit that all eu member states would implement a unified foreign policy in order to speak to the outside world in the same language .
however , in handling the issue of bosnia - herzegovina , the so - called " unified foreign policy " was for the first time met with complete failure .
from the malstrich summit until today , eu diplomacy , which has lasted as long as 10 years , is lacking .
in particular , the eu 's foreign policy can not stand the test of major events .
the different stands adopted by the member states in the us - iraq war have not only proved this point , but also once again fully exposed the fatal political defects of the eu . that is , it is prone to be separated from other big powers and destroyed by each other .
on 24 february , president bush announced in the white house that he would support the constitutional amendment prohibiting the marriage of the same sex .
this is a marked change in his ambiguous attitude on this issue over the last few months , representing an important development of us politics in an election year .
this constitutional amendment banning marriage is a very powerful political weapon in the southern part of the newly founded republican headquarters , but also plays an extremely negative role in the united states . this is a heavy scale cultural dispute aimed at splitting the will of the people , which will undoubtedly aggravate the polarization of us politics and further separate the east and west sides of the strait dominated by the liberal faction .
as far as bush himself who repeatedly claimed that he was a " gang member " but not a " separatist " during the 2000 election was concerned , his words and deeds were obviously different .
in addition , the younger generation in the united states has become more and more open in their stand on homosexuality , and this move of bush will damage the long - term interests of the republican party even though it has yielded short - term results .
bush 's new " constitutional amendment " attack can be termed the " scorched strategy " of this year 's presidential election .
bush adopted this tactic because he became increasingly weak on the two important issues of " counter - terrorism " war and economic employment , but he had no choice but to open up a new battlefield on religious and cultural issues that split the will of the people at home .
so far the united states has remained cautious in this regard .
that is to say , since maintaining the status quo in the taiwan strait can satisfy the united states ' long - term strategic goal of containing the mainland , the united states should avoid political and military conflicts with china because of encouraging taiwan independence .
it can be imagined that the united states will completely eliminate the space for holding a referendum in taiwan in accordance with beijing 's demand , but it will take some early warning actions out of its own interests .
recently , us secretary of state powell took the initiative to reiterate the established policy toward taiwan and take the initiative to express the us stand of opposing taiwan independence .
this kind of attitude has been interpreted by the outside as the purpose of curbing and preventing chen shui - bian from becoming possessed by the devil .
some us think tank personages with an official background recently made some remarks , and the united states will dispatch a large number of spy ships to the taiwan strait to detect military developments there in the near future . all these indirectly show that the united states is very concerned about the situation in the taiwan strait .
from another angle , it shows that although the united states will not completely stop holding a referendum on taiwan in accordance with beijing 's demand , it is also worried about the uncertainty of the situation in the taiwan strait during this period .
in the end , any large - scale election with one - on - one will produce only one result . either chen shui - bian will be lucky to be reelected , or lien chan will enter taiwan 's presidential palace again .
what is worrying is that under the condition of asymmetrical information dissemination , people of all walks of life on the mainland seem not to be mentally prepared for a possible victory for chen shui - bian .
if the result of the election is not what it wishes , beijing will find itself in an unnecessary passive position again .
an arab proverb says : " the chaos in one day is more terrible than the high - level government in 1,000 years . "
is this what the northeast asian countries are worried about at present ?
i think the answer is probably affirmative .
in a recent study , a well - known research and development center , which is close to washington and funded by the us government , explored four policy options for dealing with the dprk nuclear crisis , that is , engagement , containment , economic sanctions , and preemptive attacks .
the focus of the survey is the attitude of countries in the region towards these strategies .
in addition , the survey also analyzed the threat posed by the dprk 's nuclear weapons program in light of the possibility of an attack on nuclear weapons by the dprk 's neighboring countries , the possible damage done , and their fear .
china and russia feel that the danger of north korea 's use of nuclear weapons is low or very low , while japan and south koreans believe that the threat is quite great .
all the countries in northeast asia agreed to maintain contacts with north korea .
japan for its part supports containment , and other countries also believe that the containment strategy is acceptable under certain circumstances .
singapore cares very much about its international ranking . in the beginning of a year , it has paid close attention to the list of various countries in europe and the united states released by european and american institutions .
it is natural that we are on the top of the list .
however , there are also quite a lot of worries .
most people in china feel that they pay too much attention to the loss of their ranking and take pride in their ranking .
therefore , people say that we should live in a healthier way and compete with the rest of the world .
as many people looked disdain at the ranking in the past , a wonderful phenomenon emerged : people no longer regard " the world 's number one " as good news but preferred to regard it as an embarrassing thing .
however , the situation has changed over the past one or two years .
we are doubtful about the country 's long - term competitiveness , and people in all trades and professions are also worried that their rice bowls can hardly be guaranteed .
with this doubt , we are no longer so casual when we talk about it .
international competition is intense , and too little water may result in others catching up with one another and , first of all , it is easy to become a sample backward .
