according to information , those who choose to commit suicide are mostly young people aged between 15 and 19 , but many of them are young people aged 10 to 14 .
it is generally believed that academic pressure is the direct cause for children and youth to commit suicide , but studies have found that emotional problems , particularly love between men and women and problems between parents , are the main causes for local young people to find their own shortcomings .
the difference in academic pressure and expectations is of course also within the scope of communication between parents and children .
the pressure of further studies is an inevitable burden for the long term , and sometimes it is given to them by their parents and children in many times .
if parents want their children to have good results , they will take other children as a comparison . naturally , it will result in great pressure on their children to strive for higher heights . however , the channel of persuasion and communication behind the pressure is a way of measuring parent - child relations .
if the child 's performance is not ideal , his parents will condemn him or her in a silent manner , or even make the child feel disappointed , and undoubtedly push the child to an impasse of seeking help .
it is understood that many young students who need counselling are forced to enter the blind spot by excessively high expectations of their parents .
singapore 's success and rapid development have made parents feel that their children have much better material conditions than in the past . it is hard to avoid believing that their children should perform better than themselves .
usually , parents have forgotten that they are still their children , but actually their performance in various aspects may not be particularly outstanding .
when she was one and a half years old , the overwhelming majority of children were sent to the nursery of various institutions to practice a full care system , and the authorities only symbolic that they would charge a little child a week or even one month back home .
today , singapore is facing a social problem of a declining fertility rate and an ageing population .
in order to maintain a modern standard of living and to enjoy their leisure time , the younger generation has the energy to respond to the government 's call for early marriage and early child birth .
this writer has made a bold suggestion : the government should come forward to accept new - born children .
the people of our country only manage their lives , and there is no need to worry about breeding .
on the one hand , the government has set up a nursery school under a single care system and converted primary schools into whole - day schools , or even provided three meal services , thus symbolising the government 's efforts in collecting fees from citizens .
this will not only solve the employment problem of the unemployed population , but also reduce the cost of the government 's measures such as bonuses , maternity leave , quality of women and domestic helpers , and tax rebates .
what beijing needs to do is not only to play a leading role in the six - party talks but also to focus on china 's long - term interests on the korean peninsula , to prepare for a rainy day , and to start strategic deployment as soon as possible .
to put it more specifically , beijing on the one hand wants north korea to abandon its nuclear weapons . on the other hand , it starts from transforming the kim chong - il regime by guiding north korea on the road of modern civilization , lifting the danger of nuclear war in northeast asia , maintaining the status quo on the korean peninsula , and obtaining bargaining chips in long - term strategic dealings with the united states .
pyongyang is ferocious in appearance but weak inside , and in its heart it is eager to develop the economy and merge with the international community .
however , this kind of desire is often expressed in an external form that is inexcusable , irrational , and sometimes even totally inconsistent with international rules .
as a matter of fact , for some time now , beijing has used the means of influence and economic aid to force pyongyang to change its stand that is inconsistent with international rules .
but this operation still needs to be planned in an all - round way .
beijing 's aid to pyongyang should not be limited to the economic aspect , but should all the more be extended to other fields of society , and not limited to pyongyang 's giving up of its nuclear plan , it should all the more focus on the approach of introducing it to modern civilization .
