however , in january , prior to the party caucus meeting in the state of virginia , kerry suddenly took off and won the party group meetings and primary elections in the two most critical states of apollo and new hampshire .
in the following state elections , kerry basically did not lose hands , and the states that lost the hands were all because that state had its own candidates .
kerry spent only six weeks turning from a candidate with almost no future to the final candidate , and all his competitors , including gephardt , lieberman , clark , di'an , and edwards , fell in succession . this has to make people look at kerry 's political charm .
during his 19 - year tenure as senator , kerry has always supported policies on abortion and environmental protection , opposed tax cuts for the benefit of the rich , worked hard to raise the minimum wage , and hoped to resolve the problem of global warming .
his work experience in washington has demonstrated his courage to face social problems squarely , challenge authority , pursue value , and defy the interests of a small number of people .
china 's reform and opening up policy began from agriculture , and the rural residents were the earliest beneficiaries of this policy .
however , since the 1990 's , agricultural reform has basically stagnated due to the economic policy tilted toward the cities , and the gap between the cities and the countryside has become increasingly wide .
over a long period of time , china has already displayed two completely different worlds . one is a highly prosperous city , and the other is a poor and backward village .
in chinese officials ' minds , the widening of the gap between rich and poor in china 's urban and rural areas is a " question of development , " so it is still necessary to resolve it through sustained development .
in other words , china 's coastal areas and cities should continue to develop , and should not be dragged down by the rural problems .
however , when people see that some big cities can undergo minor changes a year and undergo major changes in three years , they will ask : why have some poor areas not changed in the past few decades ?
of course , the development path of the urban and rural areas is very different . this is a fact that should be recognized . however , the question is whether the rural population , which accounts for 70 percent of the country 's total population , has also received concern and attention when a large amount of funds have been invested in urban construction and given encouragement and support to the affluent middle class ?
theoretically , all previous chinese governments have paid close attention to issues related to agriculture , the rural areas , and the peasants .
however , over the past few years , the situation in rural areas has become increasingly difficult and worsened . this shows that the degree of attention given to the problem has become less and less serious .
in any country , public security , procuratorial , and law should be a symbol of justice and justice , and should also be the most important system for safeguarding social stability .
unfortunately , public security , procuratorial , and judicial organs have become a symbol of corruption in china .
the national audit office recently reported that the results of the examination of the financial expenditures of public security organs in 26 provinces and municipalities last year showed that the amount of illegal funds paid by public security organs across the country reached 16.5 billion yuan .
the confidence crisis in public security , procuratorial , and law has become open .
both the liu yong incident and sun zhigang incident and the recent " bmw " incident in heilongjiang have reflected such profound distrust .
the " bmw " incident is even more typical .
people 's concern over this problem even far exceeded their attention to sars during the sars period .
as a matter of fact , people 's concern is no longer that of the " bmw " incident itself but has expressed their distrust of the entire judicial system .
the departments concerned are very clear about this , so they have taken measures to block the media from doing so not long ago .
however , the problem is still there .
the second round of six - party talks on the korean peninsula nuclear issue ended in a widely expected result .
during this round of talks , all parties concerned conducted contacts and explorations on the peripheral issues of the nuclear crisis on the peninsula and reached consensus on holding the third round of talks and setting up a working group before the end of june this year .
however , the talks not only did not make any progress , but also gave people a feeling that the dprk should give up its nuclear weapons development plan and that the united states should ensure its political and military security after north korea renounces its nuclear program .
neither the dprk nor the united states has shown any concessions . neither has the basic stand of the two sides relaxed .
however , what attracted people 's attention was that during this round of talks , the united states showed an attitude of not rushing to solve problems and gave people the impression of " dragging on " .
this strategy demonstrated by the united states is closely related to the new development of the current international situation and to the interests it has gained in these new developments .
since roosevelt became president , the united states has never put so many company bosses in jail .
is this a coincidence , or has the public and investors endured the crime of a company and other illegal acts over the past three years , and this has caused the crime to be exposed most recently ?
the answer may not be simple , but it is a fact that many companies have recently been exposed of criminal activities .
this is a good beginning for the economic recovery , especially for restoring investment confidence .
at the end of the 1990s , it may be one of the most chaotic and difficult stages in us commercial history , and the earlier its influence is lost , the better .
the dust has settled , and the names of some companies are bound to fade away from history , and in the end they can only be found in the textbooks of the school of business .
some other companies , such as taike and mai po , will , under the leadership of their new management team , strive to restructure themselves in order to greet a new round of economic growth .
when will a new round of economic growth come ?
as cmec , you may not have any answer .
it is not necessary to do this because us federal reserve chairman alan greenspan does not know the answer .
the bush administration wants to stimulate the economy by means of idiot . on the one hand , it wants to greatly increase spending ( particularly national defense expenditures ) , and on the other hand , it wants to reduce taxes by a large margin .
internationally , the bush administration continues to promote free trade , but the trade deficit has reached a record high of $ 549 billion .
after the big tax cut , there was no marked increase in investment and consumption .
the new keyley , represented by the famous british economist gao dezhan , believes the us economy is already in a difficult position and bush 's financial and economic strategies are lacking in skill .
they believe that the so - called " putting the market law in command " is only an illusion and will inevitably bring benefits to a small number of people and suffer losses from the majority .
people have been of the view that , on a global scale , the so - called minority of profits are all in the united states , and the majority of the people who suffer losses are in developing countries .
this is not the case at present .
many people in the us economic and academic circles believe that apart from the multinational companies based on the united states , india and china are also in a prominent position in the process of globalization .
india occupies the service sector of the economy , while china occupies the sphere of manufacturing .
people have concentrated their energies on the transfer of large quantities of us capital and production equipment to china , but they have failed to see the advantages of china 's high - level and low - income labor market .
first of all , the current situation in taiwan is expected to be outside beijing 's estimation .
how beijing estimates it , only its own clear , but the estimated results can be considered by the people around the world from the open phenomena .
over the past four years , the pro-independence camp of chen shui - bian and annette lu has spoken clear - cut and acted diligently , and the taiwan independence movement has made positive progress .
in contrast , beijing , apart from her spouses , has a moderate attitude of being close to routine , and seems indifferent toward the progress of taiwan independence .
however , since the autumn of last year , it has become totally different . it seems that the cow car has changed into a cattle vehicle , which can be seen in the past few months , and its handling capacity is quite different from that of the 1990 's .
from this we can conclude that taiwan 's current situation is within its estimation .
second , it is necessary to look at foreign affairs related to taiwan .
on the development of the situation in the taiwan strait , it depends on whether or not the attitude of the united states and other major countries is closer to beijing or taipei .
as the attitude of various countries can be seen publicly , the answer is very clear .
up to now , not only have countries and beijing become relatively close , but they have a lot of concrete common ground . they have become rather distant from taipei and do not share much specific feelings with it , but they have also started to give advice on democracy in taiwan , which has been praised all along .
